5056, "(fr)The GTA vectors in on one of the destabilizing elements in Antarès, a smuggler known as Gavel."
2970, "(fr)!html <div class='blue'>GTD Intrépide<br$slash>Antarès System<br$slash>2336/10/31<$slashdiv>

<span class='blue'>The Joint Service Drone Command Program<$slashspan>

What you're about to hear is classified Level Upsilon. During the GTI Rebellion, it was revealed to top fleet officials that the branch's failed <span class='brightblue'>Joint Service Drone Command program<$slashspan> did produce one successful technology. This technology would allow the remote control of manned fighters, provided they were outfitted with the proper firmware upgrades. I don't know what GTI's ultimate goal with <span class='brightblue'>JSDC<$slashspan> was, but one rumor is that it would allow them to continue operating fighters whose pilots had been wounded or killed in action. Another, more sinister, theory is that it would allow GTI to co-opt critical OpFor craft and use them to stage assassinations and false flag attacks, possibly against high ranking GTA officers, possibly against even <span class='blue'>PVI<$slashspan> units if the technology could be adapted. Our operation focuses on this second theoretical purpose. 

Over the past several months, our efforts to bring Arris Gavel in for questioning have returned abysmal results. Therefore, we're going to turn Gavel against his employers. His old friends won't just disown him or refuse to shelter him. We want them hunting him. We intend to sully Gavel's name within smuggling groups and privateer circles so thoroughly he'll never be able to stick his head inside an inhabited star system again. At least, not without our protection."
2971, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>New Technology: GTM-37 Ballista<$slashspan>
 
We've received our first shipment of the new <span class='brightblue'>GTM Ballista<$slashspan>. Improved fuzzy-logic and ambient-radiation cancelling algorithms allow the Ballista to reliably track targets out to 2.8 kilometers. Otherwise identical to the Phoenix V, the Ballista allows our units to engage targets before hostiles can bring their own missiles to bear. The new missile's passive target acquisition abilities also shorten the reaction time of enemy pilots, lessening their chances of successfully evading the Ballista."
2972, "(fr)!html A fourteen-ship convoy was reported leaving a rally point at the Juniper Mining Complex ten minutes ago. Our objective, Arris Gavel, has been hired to fly escort for these ships. We expect them to enter an asteroid field approximately 0.4 AU from Antarès VII. They're trafficking goods that are heavily regulated under General Order 10: organic foodstuffs, Earth-produced pharma, smart manufacturing machines, and several other items put on the GTA's Restricted Trade list following the collapse of the Sol jump node. <span class='blue'>Alphas 1 and 2<$slashspan> will be deployed to the convoy transit site. The asteroid field should afford you some protection from the antiquated sensors of the convoy's freighters and escort Pies. Gavel and the gunship Vizier are already awaiting the convoy in the asteroid field."
2973, "Chasseur de Gavel"
2974, "Vizier"
2975, "Convoi de Contrebandiers"
5057, "(fr)!html Our operative has installed the proper firmware upgrades on Gavel's fighter. A transceiver hidden on the ventral hull will allow you to take control of his fighter from your Loki. <span class='white'>Press the indicated button<$slashspan> to run the hijack program on Gavel's ship. <span class='white'>Press the second button<$slashspan> to exit the program. You can toggle back and forth at will until the hijack is purged from RAM, which will take about five minutes after first executed. Make sure your Loki is a safe distance from the convoy while you're flying Gavel's fighter. <span class='white'>Press the third button<$slashspan> to completely terminate the program early. "
2977, "(fr)!html While in control of Gavel's fighter, you should have full access to flight systems, weapons, and ETS. Destroy as much cargo as possible while in control of Gavel's fighter. He flies a heavily uparmored Mustang Alpha, but don't let its durability lull you into a false sense of security. Also, be advised that the convoy's <span class='brightblue'>two sensor masks<$slashspan> will interfere with the control signal, most likely in the form of video feed distortion. Destroy the convoy's screening equipment if it becomes a big problem, but <span class='white'>prioritize cargo containers<$slashspan> for destruction. The loss of the highly valuable and irreplaceable goods will irk Gavel's masters a lot more than the downing of a few freighters and Pies."
2978, "Écran de Capteurs du Convoi"
2979, "(fr)!html After five minutes, or upon manual termination, control will return to Gavel permanently. The program will re-enable his jump drive and he will be permitted one jump before it flushes the navigation computer and cold starts the subspace drive. This will allow us a precious few minutes to talk with Gavel while he can't run away. We will track him after this first jump and you will follow. If he does not prove amenable to our proposition, disable his ship with your Disruptor guns and await a recovery transport. Be advised, if his ex-smuggler allies manage to follow him as well, you will be charged with defending the objective until he can be recovered."
2980, "(fr)!html It was imperative that Gavel be brought back alive for human intelligence purposes. He was one of our best shots at getting a handle on the Hammer of Light's collaborators in this system. Obviously, we asked too much of you."
2981, "Ne laissez pas le fait que le chasseur de Gavel soit lourdement blindé vous bercer dans un faux sentiment de sécurité. Si vous subissez des dommages de la part des chasseurs, détruisez-les immédiatement.

Si vous devez protéger le chasseur de Gavel d'une attaque, abordez la tâche comme vous le feriez pour défendre une cible légère. Les missiles ne peuvent pas être abattus comme les bombes le peuvent, alors détruisez l'attaquant dès que possible. Les Mustang Bêtas peuvent emporter plusieurs salves de missiles Frelon. 

Si vous n'avez pas pu obliger Gavel à coopérer, son chasseur sera une cible facile lorsque les tirs reprendront. Le double canon du Vizier peut détruire le chasseur de Gavel en un seul coup. Détruisez-le, ou détruisez les sous-systèmes d'armes du Vizier dès que possible."
2982, "(fr)!html Your sluggishness failed this mission. Flight recorder analysis shows no system problems, and bioscan reveals you were not afflicted with any physical ailments at the time of launch. Your problems are obviously psychological, as in you must be stupid, and you are grounded until we find a cure for it."
2983, "(fr)Do not dawdle after taking off from the Intrépide. Jump to the asteroid field as soon as you can."
2984, "(fr)!html Your departure was unauthorized. You are stricken from the flight roster until further notice."
2985, "(fr)Do not jump out of the mission area until explicitly authorized to. Look for a Return to Base directive in your mission directives list. You can also check mission goals to see if they have been failed or accomplished."
2986, "(fr)!html The objective was recovered and is already proving to be a boon for intelligence. The acquisition of Arris Gavel likely spells the beginning of the end for the smuggling rings in Antarès. The information he brings to the table will help us launch a simultaneous assault on known hideouts and shipping routes that will cause their operations to unravel.

More importantly, he brings with him knowledge of the smugglers' complicity with the Hammer of Light's operations in this system. This should shed much needed light on the HoL's objectives and their means to achieve them."
2987, "(fr)!html You failed to frame Gavel for the destruction of the smuggling convoy's cargo. His reputation is not tarnished and he has no reason to seek refuge with us."
2988, "(fr)Total destruction of the convoy's cargo is unnecessary. Destroying a single escort fighter or cargo container will set Gavel's peers against him. However, wanton destruction of the convoy will entice him to proactively seek the GTA's protection, so the more damage you can do, the more cooperative he will be. 

Destroying the freighters themselves is inefficient and will cause the convoy to panic. Pushed enough, they will enter subspace and you risk failing the mission."
2989, "(fr)!html You self-compromised at a critical point in the mission, pilot. We understand the operational conditions were unusual, but the lapse in judgement you demonstrated out there is absurd."
2990, "Ne garez pas votre Loki à moins de 2 km du convoi, que vous soyez en mode de contrôle à distance ou non. Ne faites pas voler le chasseur de Gavel vers les Loki, et ne dirigez pas de chasseurs hostiles vers eux.

Il n'y a pas de limite de portée pour la fonction de commande à distance."
