3196, "(fr)!html PVN intel says Commander Kuk, one of Ozymandias' lieutenants, is directing the attacks on the refugee outposts. Records show he favors using interceptors to soften targets up before sending in heavy assault fighters and bombers. Hopefully the day will prove you are the better tactician.

If Ozymandias decides to intervene personally with the Cardinal, we will respond with the Frontière and the Intrépide. The combined firepower of our taskforce will be enough to annihilate the Cardinal before the destroyer can finish cycling the jump engines. We hope to take the warship intact, but if Ozymandias refuses, we have every intention on demolishing his ship on the spot. Simulations indicate we can accomplish that in less than ninety seconds with the firepower at our disposal."
3197, "Frontière"
3198, "(fr)!html <span class='brightblue'>Sentry Gun (2 Pt.)<$slashspan> - Standard GTSG Cerberus armed with Avenger cannons. A good choice for close in defense of objectives. In clusters of five or more, they can be lethal to fighters, but susceptible to return fire from bombers. Not advisable for use as a first line of defense.

<span class='brightblue'>Armor Plate (2 Pts.)<$slashspan> - Repurposed cargo platforms cannibalized from nearby installations. The 604th has welded additional armor to them so they can withstand multiple Barracuda hits. Invaluable for protecting soft targets and even useful as stationary tactical shields at forward positions. Put at least <span class='white'>50 meters<$slashspan> between the panels and anything you want to protect to negate spall damage from bombs and missiles.

<span class='brightblue'>GTJ Nemesis Jamming Array (8 Pts.)<$slashspan> - Field-kit modification of the Pharos nav buoy. Prevents hostiles within <span class='white'>800 meters<$slashspan> of the jammer from achieving secondary weapons lock. Unarmored, they should not be left in the open. Be aware that CEU has reported glitches in the <span class='blue'>Nemesis<$slashspan> targeting matrix that temporarily affect friendly units as well.

<span class='brightblue'>Defense Node (10 Pts.)<$slashspan> - Large sentry mounting six launchers equipped with the MX-27 (range 0.95km, 14 sec. lock time). Slightly better armored than an Elysium transport. Vulnerable to fighter attack or capital ship weapons if unsupported."
