3184, "(fr)!html <div class='blue'>GTD Intrépide<br$slash>Antarès System<br$slash>2336/11/19<$slashdiv>

<span class='blue'>Ozymandias<$slashspan>

Intel extracted from smuggling elements has revealed Ozymandias' obsession with destroyer tech, and that he may be in possession of some. Intent has shifted from destruction of the Cardinal to its capture.

The Cardinal must be lured into a battlefield, a time and place of our choosing. An anticipated and ambitious HoL raid on Antarès' secondary tier facilities gives us this opportunity. 

Khonsu II is at the <span class='green italic'>Angel Refuge Station<$slashspan> over Antarès VI, a haphazard collection of cargo containers repurposed for long-term habitation. He is on a goodwill tour, and his status, combined with the vulnerability of the outpost, make it a likely target. Camps like <span class='green italic'>Angel<$slashspan> were never intended to become permanent homes, but the post-War strife has made relocation difficult. The $quotebox people$quote have become an uncomfortable fact of life in Antarès. Overcrowding and overtaxed life support systems make conditions inside miserable enough without warheads punching through from outside, but these camps have normally been low on the GTA's defense prioritization roster."
3185, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>New Technology: GTM-15 Siren<$slashspan>

The first production run of the <span class='brightblue'>GTM Siren<$slashspan> has been delivered. Tested and manufactured here in Antarès, we have been authorized to use our limited inventory for the upcoming operation.

The Siren offers modest gains over the Interceptor's target acquisition and homing abilities. Similar to its predecessor, simultaneous double-taps with the Siren can translate into instant PVF Seth kills if you're lucky.

Provided we can step up production and keep the facilities in Antarès secure, we hope the Siren will become a terminal bane to every Hammer of Light pilot out there."
3186, "(fr)!html <span class='green italic'>Angel Outpost<$slashspan> isn't much to look at. The central feature is a new TC-TRI class container, designated <span class='green italic'>Angel 1<$slashspan>, to which most of the refugees in the surrounding cargo crates have been moved to. Defense of <span class='green italic'>Angel 1<$slashspan> is your primary objective. We don't have the transports available for a full scale evacuation yet, but combat engineers from the 604th are on station to bolster <span class='green italic'>Angel's<$slashspan> protection. Ensign Navarre from 391st's Epsilon wing is already there. Every wing leader is being distributed <span class='white'>Command Points<$slashspan> to allocate towards their zone's defenses."
