5070, "(fr)Antarès Station suddenly comes under attack by a contingent of HoL trying to rescue their captured commander."
3453, "(fr)!html The Hammer of Light commandeered the PVD Frontière before leaving it's crew stranded at <span class='white'>Detiula Station<$slashspan>. Sadly, the Intrépide was unable to rescue the crew before the HoL forces self-destructed the station. The explosion and preceding battle left the Intrépide crippled.

The PVD Frontière has been redesignated the HLD Frontière and is now bombarding Antarès Station with torpedoes while a fleet of cruisers is whittling down the HLD Cardinal's escort. The area has already been cleared of civilian traffic. Local security, however, is active.

Ozymandias and his command crew are being held on the station itself while the rest of his crew are locked aboard the Cardinal. Witnesses are reporting that several transports have made attempts to dock with the station, likely in order to rescue Ozymandias, transport him to the Cardinal, and retake the ship. Alpha wing, your primary mission is to target and destroy any HoL transport that comes within range of the station.

Though the Intrépide is still stranded at <span class='white'>Detiula<$slashspan>, the Admiral is aborting operations and redirecting assets from all over the system, including the <span class='green italic'>GTC Senegalais<$slashspan>. If the HoL retakes the Cardinal, their offensive capability in Antarès will be effectively doubled. We can't let that happen. Good luck, pilots."
3454, "(fr)!html Alpha 1, you returned to base without authorization and as a result you abandoned your wingmen and our allies during a hostile engagement. You are a coward and disloyal pilot. You will be confined to quarters until your court martial. Dismissed."
3455, "(fr)!html You failed to prevent Hammer of Light transports from docking with the station. As a result, multiple armed militants entered the station. As of now, the station's power grid has been destroyed, and it's turrets are offline. The Hammer of Light will have little resistance to destroy or capture the most important economic target in Antarès, thanks to you, pilot. The Admiral has yet to decide if you will ever fly again."
3456, "(fr)!html You did everything you could. Despite our best efforts, the Hammer of Light simply bested us. Ozymandias out-thought and out-planned our every move. In our naivety, we handed over the PVD Frontière and doubled Ozymandias' fighting force. All the while he sat in our custody with a half-cocked zod grin.

The Admiral wants his head, but this defeat has made the political atmosphere much more complicated. GTA Command has called a session with Admiral Po. We aren't sure what they have in mind, but since we can't seem to gain any significant ground, we suspect there is little faith left in our operations. 

When the dust settles, the Admiral will devise our next steps and strategies. Until then get some rest, pilots. You fought hard and this defeat will be difficult to weather."
