5095, "(fr)The 47th defends the Iraklion Corridor from the HoL fleet while Admiral Po hunts down Ozymandias."
4046, "(fr)!html With our previous missions a success, we are finally in a position to strike back at the Hammer of Light forces. The goal is to give the Intrépide a fighting chance against the Cardinal. To do this, we must lure away as many HoL forces as possible, including the <span class='red italic'>Frontière<$slashspan>. To do this, we will make use of the Iraklion Corridor's unique ability to limit subspace travel and communications. The Intrépide will enter the corridor using a route we are confident is under surveillance. After deploying additional fighter wings, the Intrépide will exit the corridor and run silent to Novograd. Once the Frontière has entered the corridor, the Admiral will do his best to taunt Ozymandias into a fight. The <span class='red italic'>Frontière<$slashspan> and its group must remain in the corridor until their drives recharge, so we must use that time to take them down."
3577, "Contrôle Masada"
3592, "Sortie du Couloir"
4047, "(fr)!html We expect to face a numerically superior battlegroup, so we will be using our enemies' force concentration and ignorance of the battlefield against them."
4048, "(fr)!html Six of the <span class='green'>Redoubt's<$slashspan> artillery platforms have been crewed and loaded to bear. Construction was never finished on the six, and many of their subsystems were never installed. Because the platforms are essentially deaf and blind, Alpha 1 will be tasked with acquiring targets for fire support. This information will be sent to Masada Control, where it will be relayed simultaneously to all six platforms via an ECM-resistant optical signal. Lieutenant McGivers from the 422nd will set you up with several TC 2 practice targets to get you acquainted with the system."
4049, "(fr)!html We expect the forces pursuing the Intrépide to include modified Newet-class cruisers <span class='red italic'>Apep<$slashspan> and <span class='red italic'>Duat<$slashspan>. Intelligence leftover in Masada Redoubt suggests their weapons have been modified for higher output. However, they must go through a recharge cycle after long volleys. Use this to your advantage to whittle down the fleet while the cruisers maneuver for position of their next volley."
4050, "Zeta"
4051, "Theta"
4052, "(fr)!html Additional units will harry the HoL force as they make their way down the corridor. This will involve a combination of fighter sweeps and surgical strikes, mainly directed at the <span class='red italic'>Frontière<$slashspan> and her defenses. "
4053, "Kappa"
4054, "(fr)!html Alpha 1 will direct the mortar platforms in support of our defending wings. Priority targets will be those that reach Masada Control first: fighters and fast transports or freighters."
4055, "(fr)!html As the HoL strike force percolates through our defenses, our units will conduct a fighting retreat down the Corridor. Alpha 1's focus at this stage will be the destruction of HoL cruisers likely to attack Masada Control."
4056, "(fr)!html Once the <span class='red italic'>Frontière's<$slashspan> advance units have been stripped away, our forces will converge on the destroyer for the final attack. We must destroy the <span class='red italic'>Frontière<$slashspan> before she can open fire on Masada Control."
4057, "(fr)!html Ammo types:

<span class='white'>430mm Fusion Mortar (30 Salvos Available):<$slashspan> Standard armament. 1080 rounds stockpiled. At 6 per mortar platform per salvo and 6 platforms, we have enough for 30 salvos.

<span class='white'>430mm KE Impactor (90 Salvos Available):<$slashspan> Scrap metal molecularly compressed into a mortar shell to have the same mass as a 430mm Fusion Mortar. These do minimal damage and will be used for simulation and training purposes only. They will be removed from your arsenal at the beginning of combat operations.

<span class='white'>430mm Suppression (5 Salvos Available):<$slashspan> Cluster weapon. Each mortar carries three explosive submunitions. A full salvo will blanket an area approximately 1 km^3 large. The submunitions will only target hostile craft, however, calling a suppression strike danger close is considered a desperate measure. Good for softening up fighter wings.

<span class='white'>Area Disruption (3 Salvos Available):<$slashspan> Area effect EMP saturation. These can shut down targeting on even large capital ships for up to a minute. They have an area effect similar to the suppression warheads. Call these on top of yourself if you are surrounded, wait around the fire coordinates for the strike to land, then quickly reorient yourself and head for friendly units."
4058, "(fr)!html GTD Intrépide
<span class='brightblue'>Battle of <span>Iraklion Corridor<$slashspan> +25 minutes<$slashspan>

Welcome back. News of your victory preceded you. After escaping the Corridor, the <span class='red italic'>Frontière<$slashspan> did not rejoin Cardinal as expected. Recon tracked her as she ransacked an HoL supply depot before jumping to Antarès VII. She appears to be lying low to make basic repairs. 

Our battle with the Cardinal was a draw at best. Ozymandias fielded a countermeasure to our torpedoes that left us with only blob and flak cannons. We're withdrawing to the Beta Aquilae jump node to buy us time to ready our own countermeasure. Moreover, Command has relented to provide reinforcements upon our arrival. 

The <span class='red italic'>Frontière's<$slashspan> survival is unfortunate, but not immediately worrying. Kuk's desertion of Ozymandias will never be forgiven. Plus, he's unlikely to risk his mauled ship when he can repair it and vie for the crown Ozymandias is about to lose. Never mistake ambition for initiative.  

Report to the briefing room. Your skills will be required if we're to check the Cardinal one final time."
4059, "Donner l'ordre à toutes les unités amies de désactiver le Frontière aurait pu l'empêcher de s'échapper. Mais avec les dégâts que vous avez infligés, il ne pourra pas nous arrêter avant que nous engagions un combat décisif contre le Cardinal."
4060, "(fr)!html <span class='green italic'>Yuma Station<$slashspan>
Beta Aquilae
<span class='brightblue'>Battle of <span>Iraklion Corridor<$slashspan> +6 hours<$slashspan>

We picked up another EP a couple hours ago. Nothing since. It's possible there's more survivors in hiding, waiting for a chance to bolt for the node, but I wouldn't get your hopes up.

From what we've pieced together, the worst case scenario was realized. The <span class='red italic'>Frontière<$slashspan> rejoined the Cardinal and proceeded to reduce the Intrépide. Admiral Po rebuffed Ozymandias' demand for unconditional surrender. The log then records the admiral giving the order to abandon ship. Witnesses say Ozymandias deployed transports to embark on Intrépide. Seventy-nine seconds later, a cataclysmic explosion split the Intrépide in two. We believe she was scuttled to prevent capture. 

Ozymandias has wasted no time in laying claim to Antarès and its resources. With the technology and following he has picked up during his campaign there, he is in a position of uncontested power. The Hammer of Light has the upper hand now, and not just here. Everywhere."
4061, "Perdre le Contrôle Masada vous a coûté la bataille. Si la station tombe, le Frontière pourra s'échapper presque instantanément. Assurez d'abord sa sécurité, puis préoccupez-vous des autres objectifs."
4062, "(fr)!html GTD Intrépide
<span class='brightblue'>Battle of <span>Iraklion Corridor<$slashspan> +15 minutes<$slashspan>

Welcome back. Our battle with the Cardinal was a draw at best. Ozymandias fielded a countermeasure to our torpedoes that left us with only blob and flak cannons. We've jumped further in system to buy us time to prepare our response. Command is sending help, but our plans won't hinge on their arrival. The Antarès Federation has started blockading the Beta Aquilae jump node.

Our situation would feel a lot worse if it weren't for telemetry you brought back. The sight of the <span class='red italic'>Frontière<$slashspan> going up is the broken link in Ozymandias' chain the Admiral was hoping for. We just started broadcasting the video shipwide and on civilian band frequencies. The cheering on flight deck still hasn't stopped, and the PVN can rest easy knowing their comrades have been avenged. 

Report to the briefing room. Your skills will be required if we're to check the Cardinal one final time."
4063, "(fr)!html GTD Intrépide
Beta Aquilae
<span class='brightblue'>Battle of <span>Iraklion Corridor<$slashspan> +15 minutes<$slashspan>

With the <span class='red italic'>Frontière<$slashspan> at large and still combat effective, we had no choice but to but to break off battle with the Cardinal. Ozymandias fielded a countermeasure to our torpedoes that left us with only blob and flak cannons. We would stand no chance against the combined firepower of the two Typhons again. The Intrépide has retired to Beta Aquilae, and Admiral Po is facing a court-martial for the loss of Antarès.

Ozymandias has wasted no time in laying claim to the system and its resources. With the technology and following he's picked up during his campaign, he's in a position of uncontested power. The Hammer of Light has the upper hand now, and not just here. Everywhere."
