4221, "(fr)!html As the window between launch and subspace jumps could be as short as thirty seconds, we'll have to act fast if Ozymandias' flight is detected. We've earmarked <span class='brightblue'>eight Howell torpedoes with proximity fuses and special tracking instructions<$slashspan> for this contingency. Your decoy beacon will switch to an <span class='brightblue'>alternate IFF mode that will allow our own torpedoes to home in on you.<$slashspan> Use this to guide our torps around the bulk of the Cardinal so Ozymandias can't use its hull for cover. Once the torps have a clear run at the escaping transports, deactivate your beacon so the torpedoes will reacquire their original targets. Optimal coordinates for this maneuver will be uploaded to you in the event of this contingency <span class='brightblue'>(Press F12)<$slashspan>."
4220, "(fr)!html Once Epsilon deploys with the second beacon, you'll be going on the offensive. Identify and destroy Ozymandias' decoy screen to let our own salvos through. SIGINT will be monitoring Cardinal's fighter bay traffic for any sign of a mass evacuation. Admiral Po has made special preparations in the event Ozymandias attempts to flee the Cardinal."
4219, "(fr)!html Ozymandias' torpedoes won't be able to reach us, but ours will be equally ineffective as long as his decoys are in place. We're counting on you to help us maintain a fighting stalemate in the impending engagement. Ozymandias still has a meager reserve he can call on, and we expect him to throw them into battle against you. Until we can get Epsilon wing in the field, things are likely to be brutal. We'll do what we can to check Ozymandias' fighter corps by keeping his escort units and decoys busy with our own torpedoes."
5105, "(fr)!html Like our own GTM Howell, the Vasudans' Aratrum sacrifices counter-countermeasure redundancy for maneuverability and superior all-aspect tracking ability. That's what makes them faster than our bomber launched weapons. However, this also makes the Aratrums susceptible to decoys. Your beacon will mask your sensor signature with that of the Intrépide's. The beacon draws power from your weapon banks and <span class='brightblue'>requires at least a 10% energy<$slashspan> reserve to remain active. When activated, Aratrum torpedoes will track you as a target. Keep your shields up, and stay within 2 kilometers of the Intrépide or the decoy will lose its effectiveness."
4217, "Leurre"
4216, "(fr)!html Ozymandias beat us to a working torpedo decoy beacon by mere hours, and it cost us dearly at Novograd. Our Howell torpedoes were led off course by his fighters, while his Aratrums savaged our battlegroup. Engineering has signed off on the deployment of our own <span class='white'>prototype decoy beacon<$slashspan>, and you have been selected to take it into the next battle. A second prototype is being finished as we speak, and will be assigned to Epsilon 1."
