5175, "(fr)!html We've detected several wings of fighters, a sortie of Newet class cruisers, and at least one newer design out of Sahr, the Selket of which we have no data on it's capabilities. Be cautious.

Once you engage the Newets, the <span class='green italic'>GTC Bunker Hill<$slashspan> will lock on to your coordinates for a close proximity jump into the area, minimizing the damage it takes before it can engage the hostile fleet. The <span class='green italic'>Bunker<$slashspan> will serve to try and distract the Newet gunners while you bring your weapons to bear. However, if she takes too much damage, she'll be forced to retreat. You'll need to work quickly. Newets are thin as paper, but bite like a damn shark."
5174, "(fr)Sahr Shipyards"
5173, "(fr)HoL Fleet Staging"
5172, "(fr)!html Alright pilots. For those of you that are new, I'm Lieutenant Maria. Welcome to the 47th. The opportunity we've been waiting for has arrived. We've been assigned to destroy a staging area located out in the gamma quad of the system. This is one of multiple locations that the allied fleet will target simultaneously. Our primary object is complete destruction of all hostile targets."
5171, "(fr)!html We have devised a two-part strategy that will end in a direct assault on the shipyards. First we cut off system-wide support and then we assault the shipyards directly. Your squad leaders will fill you in on your roles.

A victory at <span class='red'>Sahr<$slashspan> will be the biggest victory against the Hammer of Light since their inception. The Terran government and the Emperor have put their full support toward this operation, but the burden of success rests on your shoulders, pilots.

Report to your mission briefings at once."
5170, "(fr)!html Thank you, <span class='blue'>Commander<$slashspan>. The GTD Intrépide has been an important part of this operation. Our success can be measured by the strength of our alliance.

Pilots. The shipyards once owned and operated by <span class='white'>Sahr Corporation<$slashspan> have become much more than a manufacturing facility. Since the Hammer of Light took control, they have not only increased production to supply their fleet, but they have also turned the facility into beacon of their fanaticism. <span class='red'>Sahr<$slashspan> has become one of the most heavily fortified outposts in explored space.

The outpost now features several fortifications that deter direct assault including long-range torpedo platforms, a cloud of mines, and several fortified installations. In addition, <span class='red'>Sahr<$slashspan> is home to enough of the Hammer fleet to withstand even a modest assault on it's own. If we're going to take <span class='red'>Sahr<$slashspan>, we cannot rely on brute strength. We must be clever."
5169, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>January 13, 2339<$slashspan>

Welcome to Altair, pilots. Our joint efforts with the Parliamentary Vasudan Navy have gone very well. We've taken control of the Aldebaran node and we've fortified several staging points throughout the system. We'll begin the assault on the <span class='red'>Sahr Shipyards<$slashspan> in just a few days. For the rest of our time here, Vasudan Admiral Khu will have direct operational control. Under his orders we will unseat the Hammer of Light stronghold and cut off their supply chain all at once. Admiral?"
5168, "(fr)A joint PVN$slashGTA operation attempts to crush the Hammer of Light by crippling their fleet in Altair."
5167, "(fr)Operation: Market"
5183, "(fr)!html That you were also able to prevent the Bunker Hill from taking excessive damage is also to be commended. Her crew sends their gratitude."
