5361, "(fr)The Luyten Trail"
5362, "(fr)Task Force 27 sets out for their new assignment."
5363, "(fr)!html <div class='blue'>Centaur Station<br$slash>Delta Serpentis System<br$slash>2342/03/26<$slashdiv>

<div class='blue'>Antarès Federation Agreement<$slashdiv>

Alright, everyone, your attention, please. We've got some big news to go over today, but before that, I'd like to touch on the rumors surrounding Ensign Toury. First, he is not being stripped of his commission. The GTA isn't interested in dictating what officers can or can't do on leave time. It is, however, interested in diplomatic relations with the Antarès Federation. Some of us in this room fought against them, and I understand how tempting it can be to see them as an upstart backwater. Like it or not, they've become a sovereign state in their own right. If they want to close their borders to military personnel, we have to abide by that.

Now, as for the ensign, it is true that he was caught trying to enter Antarès. It is also true that he'd booked passage aboard a ship registered to the Regulus Syndicate. Neither of those things look good for us, but the <span class='orange'>feds<$slashspan> have accepted that he was on that ship for personal reasons, not espionage. I'm not going to discuss any discipline he may or may not be subject to from our end. What I can tell you is that he's spending the remainder of his leave in Vasuda, and will be back to fleecing you all at poker when it ends.

We got lucky this time. Let me take the opportunity to remind everyone of our agreement with Antarès. They hold the jump nodes leading to four systems beyond their own, two of them quite valuable. We need that trade, so we need to stay on their good side. Just stay out of their way, and everyone's happy."
5364, "(fr)!html <span class='red'>Hostile forces<$slashspan>

Moving along...

Our allies in the Parliamentary Vasudan Navy report no activity at the Aldebaran$slashAltair node. For those of you keeping track, this marks three years without a confirmed HoL attack. However, both sides have heavily fortified their ends of the node, and reconnaissance flights are active in both directions, so the situation could change at any time. As such, General Order 14 remains in effect.

I've also been authorized to confirm the rumors out of Luyten. The Luyten New Alliance has reported Vasudan warships not accounted for by the PVN, including an unconfirmed sighting of a Newet-class cruiser. If, how, and why the Hammer has deployed forces halfway across known space is not yet known. Our working theory is that those ships have been laying doggo to keep tabs on LNA R&D.

Lastly, the Soyakaze's spooks have traced a major pirate outfit to a remote habitat in Polaris. Intelligence believes that taking them out would contribute significantly to regional stability, so the Nereid is shipping out to take over her operations in Sirius."
5365, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>Our orders<$slashspan>

Since the Nereid's air wing is still understrength, the 107th will join up with them to fill out the roster. You'll be reporting to Commander Riohs for your orientation. I know customs work isn't anyone's idea of exciting, but it is essential if we ever want to root out the corruption in Regulus' sphere of influence. A destroyer posting might not be quite as comfortable as you're used to here, so pack heavy.

The Luyten New Alliance has requested assistance in investigating the reported HoL activity in their system, as permitted by their charter. Luyten may be far out of anyone's way, but the technology coming out of that system is a valuable strategic asset. We're deploying an expeditionary force of seven cruisers under Captain Jan Varner. The PVN wants to show their flag, so two of those ships are Atens. The 508th will provide primary fighter cover for this operation. Your numbers will be supplemented by the 413th Alchemists, a small patrol squad off Karnachi Station, as well as two wings from the <span class='blue'>Vasudan 12th Battlegroup<$slashspan>.

I've already discussed this assignment with your squadron leader. Frankly, the claims of Hammer activity are difficult to take too seriously, but the LNA has also reported missing cargo and mining ships. Statistical analysis shows that they may have their own growing pirate problem, so be ready for action either way.

All personnel are heavily encouraged to familiarize themselves with their destinations in the tech room."
5366, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>Shipping out<$slashspan>

Centaur Station has been tasked with stocking up <span class='blue'>12th Fleet<$slashspan> and the Nereid with supplies. We'll be busy for the next two days, and everyone's help is required. Your squadron leaders have your assignments."
5367, "(fr)!html Good morning, pilots. Before we get started, I'd like to formally welcome our guests from the 413th. I'm Commander Kanun Jers, the 508th's liaison to Captain Varner. I'll be filling the same role for you.

We're officially flying as <span class='blue'>Task Force 27<$slashspan>, in the grand tradition of inspiring designations, but I'm sure something else will catch on in due time - hopefully something I won't have to discipline anyone for. Our primary duties will be advising and assisting the fledgling LNA navy against the Hammer of Light and seeing to civilian safety across the system. Off the record, this will likely be a straightforward assignment. Even so, the <span class='blue'>captain<$slashspan> and myself expect every flight officer in this room to conduct themselves with the utmost professionalism in their interactions with our LNA colleagues."
5368, "(fr)Centaur Station"
5369, "(fr)Ross 128"
5370, "(fr)Task Force 27"
5371, "(fr)!html The journey to Luyten will take us through Ross 128 and Laramis. The far side of the Ross 128 node is currently overseen by the PVD Ranger, so we'll rendezvous with them before jumping to the Laramis node. Once we've departed the Ranger's ZoC, we'll officially be in uncontrolled space. Our convoy should have enough firepower to scare off any outlaw threats along the way, but Captain Varner isn't taking any chances. We're enabling the <span class='white'>Rapid Transit Protocol<$slashspan> on all convoy ships, allowing us to chain jumps back to back at the expense of other ship systems. We shouldn't be around anywhere long enough for pirate forces to even get a nav fix, and taking on multiple cruisers would be an interesting tactical decision. Even so, our turret accuracy will be degraded by roughly 20%. Until we're safely in Luyten, your fighters will be on patrol to make up the difference."
5372, "(fr)Delta Serpentis"
5373, "(fr)Laramis"
5374, "(fr)Luyten 726-8"
5375, "(fr)Ranger"
5376, "(fr)!html The necessary reconfiguration of the ships' reactors also means that they'll burn through deuterium at roughly twice the normal rate. Our Aten and Leviathan elements won't have enough fuel for the trip. Fortunately, we've been allocated one of the new Zephyrus-class tankers, designation Hearst. We'll stop in Laramis for an in-flight refueling before our final jump. This will likely be the most vulnerable moment of the voyage, so stay alert."
5377, "(fr)Hearst"
5378, "(fr)!html Our destination is the prosaically-named <span class='blue'>Site 58<$slashspan>, an old Veles-class warehouse formerly in service with GTI R&D. The station's already been purged of sensitive materials, leaving it as a defensible position with copious storage space. LNA crews have retrofitted the hangar to support modern fighters.

<span class='blue'>Site 58<$slashspan> orbits around <span class='yellow'>UV Ceti<$slashspan>, the more active of Luyten's two suns. The station's hull and electronics are specifically hardened against solar flare activity. Unfortunately, the same can't be said for the human body. You're being issued modified flight suits in case of ejection, but nothing's perfect. Report any and all symptoms of possible radiation injury to sickbay <span class='white'>immediately<$slashspan>. And yes, I'm afraid there's a mandatory safety briefing scheduled after our arrival."
