5554, "(fr)!html Welcome to Wayfarer Station, everyone. She may not be much to look at quite yet, but she'll be your posting for a while, so get comfortable. I know our maintenance crews have a lot to get to, so I won't keep anyone here longer than I have to. Everyone else, please try to stay out of their way. The sooner we can get everything shipshape, the sooner we'll stop eating <span class='red'>MREs<$slashspan>.

Pilots, I'd like you to stay a moment. Everyone else, get yourselves settled in."
5555, "(fr)!html During our transit though Ross 128, we encountered two civilian transports under attack by pirate fighters. Unfortunately, the thieves escaped with a pharmaceutical shipment intended for the only remaining GTA habitat in that sector of the system. They'll now have to wait several weeks for a replacement shipment. Unfortunately, the Gregor isn't equipped to assist with their situation right now. In the future, pilots, I expect you to act quickly and decisively when civilian well-being is at stake. Let this be a wakeup call to all of you."
5556, "(fr)The bombers will try to disable the transports. Prioritize them, and the capture transport won't even arrive."
5557, "(fr)!html During our transit though Ross 128, we encountered two civilian transports under attack by pirate fighters. Thanks to your quick response, the pirates were driven off without further incident. These vultures haunting the Frontière are an unfortunate stain on the GTA's reputation. This outfit had the overconfidence to steal from civilians right under our noses, and we reminded them exactly why we're the real authority around here. While we didn't see any other action along the route, you flew your assigned escorts to the letter."
5558, "(fr)!html During our transit though Ross 128, we encountered two civilian transports under attack by pirate fighters. Thanks to your quick response, the pirates were driven off, and their leader shot down, before they could depart. These vultures haunting the Frontière are an unfortunate stain on the GTA's reputation. This outfit had the overconfidence to steal from civilians right under our noses, and we reminded them exactly why we're the real authority around here. While we didn't see any other action along the route, you flew your assigned escorts to the letter."
5559, "(fr)!html Additionally, shortly after our arrival in Laramis, Subcommander Petoph detected a disabled Proton transport. Thanks to the efforts of Ensign Assis, we were able to access her log. Apparently, the ship was taking grey-market salvage in Luyten as a pretext for observing LNA operations. The damage to the ship is consistent with Disruptor fire to her engine section, with secondary damage likely due to disengaging drive safeties. The growing scope of Syndicate operations is worrying, but unless they prove to be responsible for the missing cargo, that's not our concern."
5560, "(fr)!html The raider mines we encountered in Luyten are concerning. More so is the LNA's failure to warn us of them. The Lavoisier's&nbsp$semicolonDr. Sarno is known to use a pro-GTA voice, but it doesn't take a PsyOp to recognize her escort's leader felt differently. Unfortunately, that attitude is typical of their military. I'll be arranging a meeting with LNA Intelligence to make sure we don't have any other unpleasant surprises. I expect these mines to be less of a problem once we've received data on the shield modifications Lieutenant Kyurge mentioned. Still, keep your eyes out for more of them."
5561, "(fr)!html There is one other unfortunate matter I have to bring up. Lieutenant Weyman, before we left Centaur Station, you reported a drive line fault which delayed our departure from Delta Serpentis by several minutes. While nothing came of it this time, we're here to provide security, and response time is of the utmost importance. The Hammer of Light is out there, along with whatever's responsible for the missing cargo. Work with your deck crews to make sure this doesn't happen again.

Alright, pilots, that's all. Commander Jers has your berth assignments. Your personal effects will arrive on the next shuttle from the Reno, so get yourselves settled in before the safety brief at 1830. Your datapads should have credentials to submit maintenance requests if you need anything before then."
5562, "(fr)!html Just a moment, Commander. We came to Luyten with a standard loadout for an expedition of this size. However, LNA R&D is nearing completion on some new weapons, which we'll be able to make use of. I'd like you to check out the <span class='white'>Inventory Terminal<$slashspan> on the flight deck before your first sortie. The same terminal will let you keep track of missile expenditures and strikecraft attrition, and requisition replacements from the LNA as needed. As you fly your missions, keep an eye out for any chance to make a good impression on our hosts. Doing so will likely make them more receptive to our requests.

That's all, Commander. I won't keep you unnecessarily. You're in cabin 2-Charlie, up two decks and starboard."
