5748, "(fr)!html <div class='blue'>GTI Wayfarer<br$slash>Luyten System<br$slash>2342$slash04$slash02<$slashdiv>

<span class='blue'>Welcome aboard<$slashspan>

As the commanding officer of <span class='blue'>Task Force 27<$slashspan>, I would like to officially welcome you to Luyten. To those of us with me here on Wayfarer Station, welcome aboard. She'll be our home for the duration of this tour, so make yourselves at home. To those joining us virtually from the other convoy ships, thank you for your attention. We've got a lot to go over today, so let's get started.

I trust that you have familiarized yourselves with Luyten in the tech room database. I'd like to take the opportunity to clarify a few points and dispel some misconception I've heard going around. I ask that we hold Q&amp$semicolonA until the end."
5749, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>The Luyten New Alliance<$slashspan>

We're here as guests of the Luyten New Alliance. Whatever we as individuals may think about them, their ideas of a techno-meritocratic utopia, or the way they run the system, they are the sovereign power in Luyten. Not to put too fine a point on it, I've heard murmurs that we're wasting our time here - that we should let the LNA take care of their own problems. The simple fact of the matter is, in only a few short years, they've turned an empty backwater system into an effective research hub. GTA Command considers our ongoing cooperation mutually beneficial, and that should be enough.

Beyond that, the LNA's civilian population are still civilians, and the Hammer of Light is no less murderous for being on the Frontière. Public opinion of the GTA still hasn't fully recovered from Admiral Po's missteps in Antarès. It's an open secret that several well-known critics of the GTA sit on the LNA's board of directors. For them to have requested our assistance speaks to the seriousness of the situation. It also represents an opportunity to rebuild trust, both here and back home. We're not going to repeat Po's mistakes. We're going to work with our allies to make sure their needs are met, and we're going show them that we've learned from the past. I expect each and every officer and sailor here to follow the highest standards of conduct in cooperating with our hosts."
5750, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>The Luyten system<$slashspan>

As a binary system with two low-habitability worlds, Luyten doesn't have much in the way of natural living space. This fits well with the Luyten New Alliance's vision of a spacefaring society, but it does present some unique challenges. The LNA maintains a diverse array of habitats, some permanent, some temporarily established for specific tasks. It's a lot to keep track of, so all personnel involved with flight operations are advised to periodically review the system map.

I'd also like to take the opportunity to remind everyone of the navigational hazards in this system. Luyten's two suns give off frequent EMP noise that may disrupt fighter avionics, so be careful. The LNA also conducts gas mining operations in the Doceitov Cloud, which you may be called on to protect. It's an unpleasant environment much like the upper strata of a gas giant, but I've been told you get used to it. As always, details are available in the map room.

Lastly, STX Operations has partnered with the LNA to oversee mining operations in the system's Oort Cloud. The LNA gets to leverage STX's expertise with large-scale mining, and STX gets priority access to the raw materials out there. Of course, the recent appearance of the Hammer of Light has changed the equation somewhat. Security in the Oort Cloud is largely maintained by a paramilitary group calling itself the Second Dawn Society, which the LNA treats as a de facto system militia. Reliable information on this group is hard to come by, but what we do know has been compiled in the tech room."
5751, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>Our objectives<$slashspan>

Luyten is highly unusual by the standards of Frontière systems. The LNA drove out the usual pirates when they took over the system, and they continue to maintain order in the system's core. The LNA's ongoing scientific research means they have charted most of the subspace geography throughout the system. They've constructed permanent way stations to oversee the most popular navigational sites as well.

Of course, if everything were well in this system, we wouldn't be here. Between the Hammer of Light and mysteriously vanishing ships, the LNA's lack of seasoned pilots has become a problem. We don't know for sure who's behind the disappearances, but the attacks have been focused on isolated cargo depots, long-haul ore carriers, and similar low-value targets. That doesn't fit the HoL profile at all. The Second Dawn Society is another likely suspect, but that doesn't fit with STX's reports of their conduct, or what we know of their ethos. The LNA's working theory is that a small-scale pirate group may have survived their initial purge after all. They've taken to calling this group raiders.

Our first priority is stabilizing the situation with the Hammer of Light. The LNA is overextended trying to cover all their territory. Before anything else, we need to see to public safety. We're working to schedule our Fenris, Leviathan, and Aten elements to lend fire support to the LNA's air wing. Our own pilots, meanwhile, should expect to be deployed to escort particularly valuable shipping, such as that associated with the LNA's beam weapons program. Once the immediate situation is stabilized, we plan to transition to a more offensive posture. We're fortunate enough to count three former GTI pilots among our number. Lieutenant McPherson and our CAG both served with the Cutthroats in Antarès, while Lieutenant Commander Petoph served in a covert capacity in the <span class='white'>Great War<$slashspan>. You three may be called to gather intelligence on enemy positions, either the Hammer or the raiders.

All personnel expecting to be involved in combat operations are also to familiarize themselves with the specifications of the LNAf Tyr interceptor, the LNAe Elcano habitat, Amanu Station, and the various auxiliaries operated by the LNA. Pay special attention to the LNAct Maiman experimental cutter. Of the three operational Maimans, two mount prototypes of the LNA's beam cannons, and another is going through its shakedown period as we speak. I expect the Maiman's weaponry to be an important factor in our fight with the Hammer of Light, both as a weapon and as a target of their attention."
5752, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>Next steps<$slashspan>

Dr. Tsega Sarno of the LNA is giving an official welcome later. The LNA's research wing generally views the GTA more favorably than the central government, so long as we stay out of their hair, and Dr. Sarno is no exception. She'll be arriving at 1120 hours station time. Until then, feel free to get a head start on the tech room, or familiarize yourselves with Wayfarer Station. She's an older facility, so try not to overwhelm the net with maintenance requests."
5753, "(fr)!html Good morning, pilots. I hope you're all getting settled here in Luyten, but we've already got a situation developing. The Luyten New Alliance has asked for our assistance, and your names are up."
