5758, "(fr)!html The issue at hand concerns the Chicxulub, one of the LNA's Maiman-class cutters. Built here in Luyten, these ships are host to a number of experimental weapons, chief among them a <span class='white'>photon beam emitter<$slashspan> running along the ship's spine. The Maiman beams are based on data gathered from the SD Lucifer, just like the main guns of the Hades superdestroyer. Unlike the Hades, the LNA designed their hardware from the ground up rather than trying to emulate the Shivan originals. They plan on conducting a series of tests to prove the viability of their prototype, but there's been a hitch."
5759, "(fr)Test Targets"
5760, "(fr)LNA Weapons Range"
5761, "(fr)Temporary structure"
5762, "(fr)!html The LNA set up a temporary weapons range near the Doceitov Cloud, in hopes that the inaccessible location would deter onlookers. 30 minutes ago, a Vasudan force decided to dash that hope. They've been holding position 15 klicks out from the range, under ECM from a nearby Imhotep science cruiser. If that wasn't enough to confirm their allegiance, visual inspection has confirmed the existence of one Newet and one Selket-class cruiser, possibly the HLC Taweret which disappeared in Altair three years ago. They're backed up by an Aten and an unknown number of fighters.

Too many of our assets are tied up providing convoy escort to launch an assault against this fleet. They seem content to just observe so far, but that's liable to change when the test starts."
5763, "(fr)Hammer Of Light"
5764, "(fr)!html The Chicxulub is commanded by one Captain Bethany Hughes, and the experiment is being overseen by Dr. Agamas Vade, a particle physicist with a history in weapons research. Both officers agree that the Hammer ships are unlikely to gain any useful information at this distance, and have indicated that they do not intend to abort the test. Captain Varner believes that a show of strength is our best option against the HoL at this time.

That's where you come in. The LNA has little experience against this enemy, so they've asked us to provide security. Subspace topography near the <span class='yellow'>Cloud<$slashspan> will keep the cruisers from jumping to attack to the range, but that won't be any problem for their fighters."
5765, "(fr)!html I'm certain you all understand the importance of what the LNA is developing here, and just how bad it would be if the Hammer of Light got their fanatical little hands on it. <span class='white'>Do not let that happen.<$slashspan> Be prepared for Hammer freighters or transports trying to dock with the Chicxulub, and take any means necessary to stop them. It is also possible that the local raiders may be cooperating with them, as was the case in Antarès, so regard any unexpected Terran ships as potentially hostile until proven otherwise.

You've had three days to learn where the flight deck is, so get moving. You launch in 15."
5766, "(fr)Capture operation?"
5767, "(fr)!html Alpha, here's the situation. Long-range scanners have not located the Chicxulub anywhere in this system. We believe the Hammer may have disabled its transponder mid-jump. We've redirected the 413th and Rho wing to investigate the most likely exit points, but without a SUTRAC fix, we don't expect them to find anything. Captain Varner is deploying cruiser assets to cover the intersystem jump nodes, and we're placing all available pilots on hot standby.

The theft of the beam prototype may represent the start of a very dark chapter in Luyten. We're operating with limited information here, so be prepared for anything. Take five to catch your breath, then report to the flight deck. We'll all need our wits together if we're going to get through this."
5768, "(fr)A Satis has a strong turret screen, and coming to a stop will just get you killed. Try performing strafing attacks, ideally with missiles. Your wingmates can cover you from the enemy fighters. Alternatively, try splashing the Hammer fighters quickly, then sending all your ships after the freighter to defeat it in detail.

The raider's drones will target the Hammer ships as readily as anything else, so try to pay attention to what they're up to. Letting them get hits on the Defiler will help distract its turrets. You can press $G$ to target a ship attacking your target, or $J$ to target your target's target. Both of these controls can be put to good use here."
5769, "(fr)!html Pilots, you really screwed this one up. This was our first joint operation with LNA forces, and it should have established the foundation of a strong working relationship. Instead, you showed the LNA that we don't know what we're doing. Anti-GTA voices within Luyten are already calling for our removal from the system. Like it or not, we're here as their guests, and you just made us unwelcome.

We will all have to put in effort to establish trust with the LNA. In the short term, I've instructed our technicians to set up a training regimen against simulated raider craft. The next time you go up against these ships, you will be ready.

Dismissed."
5770, "(fr)Do not stray to far from the Chicxulub. Xi wing will attempt to protect it on their own, but may be overwhelmed without your assistance. The Chicxulub will call for help if it starts taking damage - don't ignore those messages.

Remember, the Hammer of light wants to capture the Chicxulub, and will not engage it directly. The raiders have no such compunctions. Make sure to prioritize threats appropriately. You can press $G$ to target a ship attacking your target, or $J$ to target your target's target. Both of these controls can be put to good use here.

You may also be able to bait the raider ships into attacking Defiler for you. Fly close to them so they target you, then fly back to Defiler and let its turrets do the dirty work."
5771, "(fr)!html Welcome back, Alpha wing. While you were in subspace, LNA Command reported that the Chicxulub arrived safely at Amanu Station. You faced considerable resistance - not only from the Hammer of Light, but also from these mysterious <span class='red'>$quoteraiders$quote<$slashspan>. Your diligence and quick thinking in the face of a highly unstable situation is to be commended.

We still don't have any information on the HoL's objectives in this system. While you were defending your objective, the two groups engaged each other, and the raiders destroyed three of the four Hammer ships in the EZ. This establishes beyond reasonable doubt that the two sides are not working together. The Hammer is clever and sneaky, but throwing away cruiser assets for a simple deception crosses the line into stupidity.

The confirmed presence of Hammer of Light forces in Luyten, and the capabilities the raiders have demonstrated here, indicate that the situation in Luyten is far more dangerous than GTA Command expected. We have dispatched messages through the Luyten$slashLaramis subspace relay, and our Vasudan colleagues have done the same. Given the distances involved, it may be some time before fleet assets can arrive. We will keep you updated as soon as we have anything definite to go off of."
5772, "(fr)!html On a more positive note, the Chicxulub was able to recover the ejected pilots of Xi wing before its departure. While combat spacecraft aren't easily replaceable this far out on the Frontière, they're far more replaceable than pilots."
5773, "(fr)!html We've assigned the unknown raider ships you encountered reporting names drawn from historical Brittonic and Welsh mythology. The fighters have been designated TF Camma, and the large ship TCv Ker-Ahes. We don't have the human resources out here to perform a full-scale tactical analysis of your flight data, but we do know that the Camma carries no shields or secondary weapons, and we believe that the Ker-Ahes has some degree of electronics warfare capability. Since the Camma appears to be uncrewed, we suspect the larger ship may control them directly. Taking it out is therefore a top priority.

Reconnaissance flights to track down the Ker-Ahes and identify the Hammer's base of operations will begin over the next few days. Praxis review of the preliminary schedule will begin at 1830, and I want all of you there. This is a complicated situation, pilots, but I have every faith in your ability to handle it.

Dismissed, pilots."
5774, "(fr)This new enemy isn't just going to go away. Stay vigilant."
