5952, "(fr)!html Sublieutenant Kinson, I'd like to take this opportunity to commend your pilot recovery maneuver during the retreat. It is my opinion that you displayed bravery and quick thinking under fire, and I've asked Captain Varner to see that you are properly rewarded for it when we've regained contact with the GTA."
5953, "(fr)!html While the presence of raider ships in Laramis is not, in and of itself, surprising, the confirmation of a second Ker-Ahes-class vessel is of some concern. So are the additional fighter classes you encountered. We've designated the superiority fighters Ankou, and the heavy fighters Iseult. The Ankou carries Disruptor weaponry in addition to the standard raider cannon, while the latter mounts long-ranged anti-shield missiles. Like the smaller Camma, neither ship seems to carry its own pilot.

Worse still are the capabilities the <span class='red italic'>Caerwent<$slashspan> demonstrated. Our working theory is that the raiders captured the <span class='red italic'>Warshawski<$slashspan> and forged outgoing transmissions to maintain the illusion of normalcy in that system, and similarly faked Captain Petrillo's declaration of quarantine. 

We're still no closer to re-establishing contact with Terran Command. As far as the outside world is concerned, there's nothing unusual going on here besides a virulent but non-suspicious plague outbreak. In the mean time, we're on our own.

You flew well today, pilots. Keep it up. We'll need that to get through this. Dismissed."
5954, "(fr)!html Welcome back to Luyten, pilots. The Ifrit has just transited the node with some of the Lavoisier's crew aboard. Unfortunately, the ship itself is now in raider hands, along with its technology, Dr. Sarno, and, presumably, the <span class='green italic'>GTSC Warshawski<$slashspan>. Not only did we fail to complete our objectives, it is likely the raiders will be able to adapt its equipment for their own use.

This mission represents an institutional failure on multiple levels. We should have been prepared for raider forces in Laramis. We should have gone in with better intelligence. We shouldn't have gambled such a valuable ship without a plan to deny it to the enemy. We're no closer to contacting Terran Command, and the balance of power has tilted even further in our enemy's favor.

If we don't find a way to take some pressure off ourselves, we may be forced to surrender to these raiders. Anyone with a bright idea, please bring it forwards."
5955, "(fr)!html Try to keep as many fighters alive through the raider ambushes as possible. Respond quickly when they call for help. If you see an enemy ship targeting one of yours, you have a golden opportunity to get in position for a missile while it's distracted.

