6151, "(fr)!html The LNAct Chicxulub exited subspace with the civilian transport Opportunity in tow twenty minutes ago, and Amanu Station reports the Lambda tugboats safely in their ZoC. On both a strategic and a moral level, today represents a significant success. The supplies that we recovered will be pressed into service by us, not against us, and Elias Pendergast, his crew, family, and pilots, are now safely aboard Wayfarer.

The Opportunity is a Wyvern-class transport modified with back-to-back jump drives, ostensibly as a defense against piracy. It's an open secret that these modifications are commonly employed by smugglers, but, frankly, that isn't our concern right now. Ensign Assis, you speculated that the Opportunity's escorts may be associated with the Regulus Syndicate criminal organization. Be that as it may, we can't be picky about our friends. We have an opportunity, no pun intended, and we intend to take advantage of it.

In light of the ongoing node blockade, Pendergast's contractors have expressed an interest in helping out. We intend to use them to supplement our security patrols at Wayfarer and free up fighters for other duties. Once the Opportunity itself has been repaired, we intend to ask her crew to lend a hand with our logistical train. We're all in this together, and I expect these people to be extended every courtesy.

You did well out there today, pilots. Dismissed."
6150, "(fr)!html But we have to look ahead. We're now playing host to a wing of <span class='blue'>private security contractors<$slashspan>, possibly associated with the Regulus Syndicate criminal organization if Ensign Assis' speculation is to be believed. They aren't any happier about the situation with the Opportunity than we are. Fortunately, they seem to understand how tenuous our situation is. We intend to use them to supplement our security patrols at Wayfarer and free up fighters for other duties.

A single transport isn't going to sway the course of this war, but we all swore an oath to protect the civilians under our care. Think about what happened today and how you can do better going forward, then get ready for the next op. Dismissed, pilots."
6149, "(fr)Dumbfire missiles, like the Dust Devil, are a strong answer to light capital ships. If the Iseult heavies give you trouble, send Delta wing to attack them."
6148, "(fr)!html Pilots, it's unfortunate that the raider gunship was able to outmaneuver you, but without a proper <span class='blue'>SUTRAC<$slashspan> fix, we have to call off the search. It appears that they were well-prepared to run the circuit, and may have used sprint drives to boost their subspace maneuverability. While there isn't much you could have done about that, tactical review suggests you had more than sufficient firepower to destroy the gunship before it could dock. Since you didn't, the Opportunity and her civilian passengers are now in raider hands."
6147, "(fr)!html We'll launch in four hours. Alpha, make sure you're familiar with the specifications of the Tyr before then. I want everyone at their best today! The raiders have us off-balance, and we need to seize every available opportunity to restabilize the strategic picture.

Dismissed!"
