We've also received a shipment of the DustDevil next-generation dumbfire missile. Designed by the LNA and subcontracted to STX Exploration for production, the DustDevil inflicts significantly greater damage than its predecessor, especially against shielded targets.

Our stock of both new systems is very limited, and we don't know when the LNA will be able to provide more. Wing leaders, make them available at your discretion."
6124, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>New Technology: LNAf Tyr<$slashspan>

Per our agreement, the LNA has made available a small number of their Tyr interceptors. The Tyr's spaceframe is derived from a racing ship, and with a maximum velocity comparable to the GTF Valkyrie, it shows. In keeping with the LNA's ethos, the Tyr also mounts advanced avionics and an observer seat that make it suitable in customs, scientific survey, or search-and-rescue roles as well.

While the Tyr's small size does give it a thin target profile, it dramatically limits the ship's secondary reserves as well. Choose your loadouts carefully when using them."
6123, "(fr)!html <div class='blue'>GTI Wayfarer<br$slash>Luyten System<br$slash>2342/04/15<$slashdiv>

<span class='blue'>Ongoing blockade<$slashspan>

Good morning, everyone. I'd like to begin by addressing the rumors going around, about a raider blockade of the jump nodes out of this system. These rumors are true. Enemy ships and mines have attacked every probe we've sent through the Laramis node, and they have similarly blocked off the nodes to Barnard's Star and Wolf 359 for unknown reasons. We believe the raiders are using forged transmissions to maintain the appearance of normalcy. We have no evidence of the real Captain Petrillo being complicit in the falsified plague reports, and they have agreed to a full audit of the Gregor's comm system.

A full-strength deployment through the Laramis node could likely break through the blockade, but would leave us without sufficient forces to protect civilian shipping and habitats here. We simply can't justify putting so many lives at risk without any guarantee of success. Instead, we'll be focusing on fortifying our position here in Luyten. We're working with Amanu Station to consolidate civilian assets at defensible locations. It's no secret that the ongoing crisis has given anti-GTA voices within the LNA fresh ammunition, but their military officials, at least, recognize that we're better off together than separately.

In the immediate term, we need to ensure that production of fuel and ammunition can continue for the duration of this conflict. I'm deploying every fighter pilot we have to that end today. Before we get to that, I'd like to go over a few points first."
