6606, "Blocus"
6607, "(fr)!html The target of this operation is Patmos Station, a former GTI black site. As far as I can tell, it started life as a civvy R&D facility. GTI probably commandeered it for a similar purpose, so it should have the backdoor we need. My contact managed to restart the station's systems before the security software kicked them off, so I'm going to board the station and present it with my old GTI credentials.

To minimize exposure, I'm keeping this op to a single fighter - a Zeus or a Tyr, something with a RIO seat. As far as anyone besides the three of us know, you're taking a technician to check out a malfunctioning sensor buoy. We'll get in, send our message, and get out before anyone's any the wiser."
6608, "(fr)!html We should have things wrapped up before the raiders detect us, but a good spook never leaves anything to chance. We're going to set a trap. The station is ringed by twelve sentry guns upgraded with Prometheus cannons. My contact has written a patch that will tell the guns to attack anything not positively identified as friendly. While I'm on the station, you'll scans the guns to upload it. If the raiders do somehow track our jump, that will buy a few more minutes for our message to get out. We'll be on our own, so get as many sentries online as you can.

If this backdoor lets us contact Delta Serpentis, it's our best hope of turning the situation here around. We're launching in fifteen minutes, so let's get suited up."
6609, "Raiders éventuels ?"
