6612, "(fr)!html Welcome back to Wayfarer, <span class='blue'>Commander<$slashspan>. I wish it was under more pleasant circumstances.

Whatever <span class='red'>Captain Varner<$slashspan> was planning, his secrets died with him. Your fighter sensors did not log any escape pod launches from Patmos Station, nor any outgoing subspace translations. Long-range sensors show Morgens gunships processing what's left. We're forced to conclude that, if the raider attack didn't get him, their salvage machinery did.

Our best lead just went traitor and died. It's a hell of a thing, especially now. Morale's already low after our defeat at the scrapyard, and our working relationship with the LNA is already strained. Privately, <span class='blue'>Commander<$slashspan>, I'm afraid this may be more than our little group can take.

Don't discuss anything that happened today with anyone until I officially break the news. Dismissed."
6613, "(fr)There's only one of you, but there are 12 sentry guns. Try to reboot as many of them as you can. Shunt energy from guns to shields to increase your survivability. Once you've scanned a gun, turn away from it and hit your burners to minimize the damage you take. Pressing F12 will highlight all the unscanned guns, so you can approach your next target while avoiding fire from the previous one. The $quoteTarget Object In Reticle$quote control ($Y$) can help here.

The Ys-class bombers are the biggest threat, so try to take them out. The stealth fighters will whittle down your sentry screen, but are easily destroyed by primary fire. Any time you're not shooting at enemy fighters, try to keep your guns on whichever Ker-Ahes has taken more damage."
6614, "(fr)!html Welcome back to Wayfarer, Commander. I wish it was under more pleasant circumstances.

<span class='red'>Captain Varner<$slashspan> never disclosed any intention to tinker with your long range communications. That goes beyond $quotepreserving operational security$quote into outright deception. We lost contact with you after you jumped, and were trying to reestablish contact the entire time. When your fighter rebooted, it automatically synced up with our command network, and I heard as much of <span class='red'>Varner's<$slashspan> conversation as you did. There will certainly be an investigation when we're back in GTA space, and you should expect to get caught up in it. I'd consult with the JAG's office, but I doubt you'll come under any serious suspicion. You followed lawful orders to the letter, up until the point where they compromised your survival... which brings me to my second point. We've reviewed the targeting patch you uploaded on <span class='red'>Captain Varner's<$slashspan> orders, and discovered it had a secondary payload which would have painted your fighter as hostile. We can only assume he always intended to $quotesanitize$quote you and commandeer one of Patmos' other fighters for the jump home.

Whatever <span class='red'>Captain Varner<$slashspan> is really up to, he isn't talking. Our working theory is that he had been a double agent the whole time, and had a change of heart when the blockade started. If so, the intelligence failure is concerning, to say the least, but that's a problem for later. In the short term, a conference of captains is being convened, where I expect to receive an acting promotion to his old role. If that's the case, I intend to augment my staff with survivors from the Eudora. My top priority will be strengthening our ties with our allies throughout this system to free up assets for offensive operations, and I'd like you to submit a proposal for how we can be accomplish that objective. It's never been clearer how desperately we need to regain control of the situation.

I'm sorry, commander. It's a hell of a thing to find out like this. We've got enough on our plate fighting our enemies without our own leadership trying to kill us, and the two of us will need to work even more closely in the coming weeks. As for what becomes of <span class='red'>Varner<$slashspan> after all this... I suppose that's up to the courts to decide. He hasn't offered any new intelligence yet, but if that changes, you'll be the first to know."
6615, "(fr)!html On a more positive note, I'd like to commend your solo destruction of an enemy AWACS. When you've rested and the situation has normalized, I'd like you to prepare a report on the tactics you used in that attack. Perhaps there's something there we can adapt. Nicely done."
