7216, "(fr)Let's go over how it works. Switch to your bank of Locusts. I'm going to generate a couple more drones. You'll notice that aspect lock does not begin immediately like it does for the Siren. You'll need to hold the trigger down to activate the tracking system. Go ahead and try it now."
7215, "(fr)With this new targeting system, the Locust is capable of independent drone tracking. What this means is that you can lock multiple targets at once. By delivering a killing payload to several targets, we believe we can bring the average drone kill count to four drones per pilot every 30 seconds."
7214, "(fr)Enter the Locust. We ripped the original ultraviolet aspect tracker out of the Hornet during conversion and replaced it with a subspace analytics package. This thing reads drone datastreams like a book."
7211, "(fr)Realistically, most pilots average one drone kill every 15-30 seconds depending on the chaos of the EZ. By then, more drones have likely arrived to keep the numbers up."
7210, "(fr)Sirens take a little over two seconds to acquire aspect lock and a further two second cool-down between volleys. The best pilot with manual control of targeting systems and multiple banks of Sirens can rack up one kill every two seconds, assuming they have no trouble getting a lock."
