7399, "(fr)Welcome back, commander. Between this op and the Gallaecia, the LNAf Tyr and the Thot you flew in Antarès, you're racking up an impressive resume of unconventional craft. You came out of there with invaluable information about INEDAM, and you destroyed the refining equipment inside the asteroid before INEDAM could discover and subvert it.

Thanks to you and the Corporal's leadership, we have a more thorough understanding of the timeline surrounding the INEDAM construct. We now know that INEDAM became active in the Iraklion Corridor when the lead researcher attempted to dispose of it. It seems the construct followed its new orders for a time, but then refused or failed to the destroy itself once it left Antarès. Instead, it came here to Luyten, where it united with the AI core being developed here on Vostok. INEDAM's ability to make the transit unassisted indicates that it either had some autonomous systems separate from the AI core, or that it was assisted by GTI elements. Either way, it reached Luyten and laid doggo while it gathered its strength."
7400, "(fr)We have strong evidence that there was some conflict aboard the Vostok installation concerning INEDAM's programming. It is difficult to say how this may have impacted INEDAM's behavior. Nevertheless, between your findings here, Varner's testimony about the INEDAM program's changing objectives, and the solar radiation here in Luyten, it is safe to say that INEDAM's AI contains many different, potentially unstable aspects. Additionally, Varner's claim that the OPHOSIS research was used in INEDAM seems to hold up."
