7627, "(fr)With the destruction of the Duamutef, we lost not only a potential new ally but also vital information on the Hammer of Light and what they are doing out here in Luyten. Hammer defections are exceedingly rare and I'm disappointed we could not capitalize on that opportunity. Flight records show it was our mistake and with more cover, the Duamutef would have survived."
7626, "(fr)!html You did well in an uncertain situation. While we were unable to locate the INEDAM manufacturing facility, what we discovered is potentially even more strategically relevant. The sensor data gathered by the Chicxulub will be invaluable in determining the capabilities of this new installation and how the Taweret came to take advantage of it.

What we do know is that the installation does not match Terran, Vasudan, or Shivan technology, and is radically dissimilar to all known Ancient relics. We have to conclude that the artifact originates with another, previously unknown, species. Apparently, the LNA had a provisional designation set aside for such a discovery, so we're calling it the Lascaux device. While the artifact is subspace-based, its operating principles are totally unlike our own drives, or so I've been told.

While the scientists over at Amanu try to make sense of the Lascaux device, we've still got a manufacturing station to find. If anything, what we've learned about the Taweret makes it even more important that we make contact with GTA Command. Beyond that, Holly bringing in supplies through the Lascaux makes a disturbing amount of sense, and goes a long way towards explaining why they haven't seemed to have the same supply issues we have.

As for the <span class='red italic'>Duamutef<$slashspan> and her crew, they're currently parked at the coordinates we sent. Whether they're on the level or not, the <span class='blue'>Captain<$slashspan> doesn't feel comfortable bringing a Hammer cruiser to our doorstep without precautions. We're planning a sortie with the PVN to meet and discuss terms. Infighting among HoL sects is rare, but not unheard of, and a Newet would be a valuable ally against both of our opponents. While I'm not about to start rolling out the welcome mat, we can take ally we get. Their captain hasn't taken a Terran name, and the computer suggested <span class='blue'>Captain Nakith<$slashspan>, so that's what we're going with.

Scouting operations to locate the drone hub resume in one hour."
