7618, "(fr)Pilots, let's get started.

Now that we know the true nature of our enemy, we know what to look for. The manufacturing facility would be large and fully autonomous. The energy output of such a facility should be unmistakable, and the fact that we haven't noticed such a signature on our sensors over the last few weeks is cause for concern. However, if we can find it and destroy it, then we can finally get out of this system."
7617, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>INEDAM in Luyten<$slashspan>

If any of you think that's too noble for GTI, you'd be on to something. The INEDAM core was assembled in Antarès, specifically the Iraklion Corridor, for secrecy. Secrecy being an expensive luxury right now, the details are available in the tech room. What you need to know right now is, after the Hades' Rebellion, a fight broke out in the Iraklion over the technology. Apparently, the core activated during the fighting and fled to protect itself. Why it attacked now is currently unknown, but it's possible that the solar flare activity may have disrupted its onboard AI.

Whatever INEDAM's ultimate motives, with this new insight into our enemy, we believe we have come up with a plan to fight back. Captain Rostami will fill you in at your mission briefings. Thank you."
7616, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>The raiders' secret history<$slashspan>

We've known for a while that the raider ships were computer controlled drones. What we didn't know was who was controlling them, or why. According to <span class='red'>Captain Varner<$slashspan> - and this has been corroborated by intel gathered at a previously hidden GTI construction facility - the drones are not controlled by anyone. At least, not anymore.

The <span class='red'>$quoteraiders$quote<$slashspan> are part of a GTI project called INEDAM, short for <span class='red'>Intersystem Entry Defense Automaton<$slashspan>. The project developed a self-sustaining drone manufacturing facility and AI controller, the latter of which is very much against interstellar law. This project began in the <span class='orange'>14 Years War<$slashspan> as a weapon to wipe the Vasudans off the map, but later transformed into a Shivan spoiler weapon. In the event that we lost that war, INEDAM would activate. Its orders were to contain the Shivan-controlled territory, gaining control of jump nodes system by system. Once containment had been achieved, it would start constructing a fleet to strike back. Like the Ancients before us, humanity would offer what aid we could to our eventual galactic successors."
