7973, "(fr)!html <div class='blue'>Amanu Station<br$slash>Luyten System<br$slash>2342/06/03<$slashdiv>

Welcome aboard Amanu Station. I'm Security Director Hifumi Abe. I'm in command of Amanu's air wing and the LNA's security division. I wish your time here had come under better circumstances, and I'm sorry for the loss of the officers, squadmates, and friends at Wayfarer. We will do everything we can here to accommodate you.

I've spoken with Commander Jers about where things stand, and I'll let her go over the situation from here. Commander?"
7974, "(fr)!html Thank you, Director Abe.

I'm going to be straightforward. We're not in a great spot. The leading theory is that the INEDAM attack at Wayfarer was retaliation for the theft of data from the Gallaecia. We're not sure if the AI was trying to limit our research into that data, or if it saw us as a greater threat after that operation. Either way, this is another instance where our cooperation with the LNA has paid off. Wayfarer was lost, but the data was safe here at Amanu. In fact, it has revealed some intel that you'll hear about in your briefings at 0300.

I know we need time to grieve for our losses. Unfortunately, time is what have the least of right now, so make appointments with ship counsel between sorties if you need. For now, we must focus on the task at hand - stopping INEDAM drone production, or finding a way to get a message out of Luyten to warn GTA Command."
7975, "(fr)!html Thanks to the Chicxulub's scan of the artifact we discovered out beyond the Oort Cloud, we may have a lead on how to achieve the latter objective. I've got a team looking at that right now, with the assistance of our new friends aboard the HLC Duamutef. Until that's ready, we'll continue to focus on the former - stopping drone production. Our next operation will be the largest joint operation since we arrived here, and we'll need everyone at their best. Have a meal, talk to someone, and get yourselves fit for duty. As I said, briefings are at 0300. Don't be late."
7976, "(fr)!html Alright, sorry I'm late. We had some last minute changes to the plan. Let's get going, because you're in the air in 90 minutes.

It took a while, but we finally cracked the Gallaecia data. There's still a ton of information to sort through, but we discovered transmission logs with tracebacks. Basically, the drone transmission network has been laid bare for us, so we threw a few math geniuses at it and they came back with one location that seems to be the central hub of INEDAM activity."
7977, "(fr)!html According to the data, the transmissions center around the Doceitov Cloud - more specifically, deeper within the cloud than the LNA has yet to explore. The higher ups, including Commander Jers, have a high degree of confidence that the drone manufacturing facility is here.

