7988, "(fr)!html Your scans of the nav system show that IN.E.D.A.M.01 has been lying dormant in the <span class='yellow'>Cloud<$slashspan> for several years. However, there is one period of time in the navigation data that shows severe corruption. That time period matches up with LNA data of a massive solar spike that swept the system a few years ago. The current theory is that this event may have been what actually triggered the AI to begin the Active Denial program. Good find."
7989, "(fr)!html Your scans of the hangar, however, are deeply troubling. The data suggests the manufacturing and launch capacity greatly exceeds even the expectations put forth in the GTI data. If we can't put a stop to this machine, we may be entirely overrun."
