8228, "(fr)!html During the opening stage of the engagement, one of the hydrogen tanks was hit, taking three of the Elysiums on station with it. The two remaining transports are moving personnel to the Ifrit, but over 200 personnel are still trapped on the refinery. We'll reroute ships from other evacuation sites as they become available.

Your sole priority is protecting the station, the Ifrit, and the transports until everyone's safely away. INEDAM seems focused on the station, but the LNA pilots have reported some drones breaking off to harass the evac ships. Per Captain Jers, no GTA ship is to engage IN.E.D.A.M.01 directly. We can't risk it deciding to accelerate its timetable while Amanu Station is still vulnerable."
8229, "(fr)!html Alpha and Bêta, once you've arrived, the LNA will pull back to protect the Ifrit, leaving the Lambda transports for you. The Lavoisier is also en route, since INEDAM still can't distinguish its holographic decoys from real fighters. Be advised that, if the refinery goes down, the raw gasses on board will certainly ignite. If that happens, all ships are to jump out <span class='white'>immediately<$slashspan> before the shockwave hits. You won't have time to get away on conventional thrusters.

Get to your ships, don't do anything reckless, and bring those people home. Good luck."
