8360, "(fr)Pilots, there was nothing you could have done to save the GTM Gregor. We went in expecting a skirmish with a Dahut group, not a gunship strike ending with the direct involvement of IN.E.D.A.M.01 itself. Today was a bloodbath, but it wasn't your fault."
8361, "(fr)!html During the engagement, Captain Petrillo gave the order to abandon ship, disregarding Captain Jers' orders to wait for a Rakhsh deployment. The <span class='blue'>Captain<$slashspan> had hoped to recover the spaceframe for future evacuations, and regrets that her stubbornness confused the situation further. She's expressed her thanks that your quick thinking, and Captain Petrillo's, allowed some of the Gregor's passengers to escape. The GTFr Reno has their coordinates and is completing pod recovery as we speak."
8362, "(fr)!html During the engagement, Captain Petrillo gave the order to abandon ship, disregarding Captain Jers' orders to wait for a Rakhsh deployment. The <span class='blue'>Captain<$slashspan> had hoped to recover the spaceframe for future evacuations, and regrets that her stubbornness confused the situation further. She's taking personal responsibility for the loss of Gregor's escape pods and their passengers."
8363, "(fr)!html The materiel INEDAM expended in this engagement far outweighs what it could possibly gain from salvaging the Gregor. We believe it was motivated by something other than simple resource-gathering. The simple explanation is that it mistook Gregor for a warship and prioritized it accordingly. However, guncam footage from your fighters shows that INEDAM treated the Gregor's escape pods as primary targets, unlike at Wayfarer, where it only engaged them opportunistically. Considering <span class='red'>Captain Varner's<$slashspan> testimony about INEDAM's adaptability, it seems likely that it has come to understand morale. If escape pods are now on its priority roster, that likely extends to search and rescue shuttles. We'll need to extend fighter cover to them as well. Captain Jers will instruct sickbay to make Grade A stims available to anyone who needs them.

IN.E.D.A.M.01 jumped out as soon as it had finished deploying bombers. This ability to chain jumps is sometimes seen on specialized ships, like the Rakhsh fast tugboat, but installing it on warships is currently beyond the capabilities of GTA or even PVN engineers. IN.E.D.A.M.01 hadn't displayed this capability before today, leaving us with the worrying possibility that it has recently modified its own engines to support it."
8364, "(fr)!html If there's any silver lining to be had, it's that these evacuations will be wrapping up soon. There simply aren't that many stations remaining unaccounted for. While we'll need to factor the loss of the Gregor into our timetables, we expect to have Luyten's civilian population aboard the Elcano habitats and safely in the Oort Cloud before IN.E.D.A.M.01 is ready to strike Amanu Station.

Rest up, pilots. Evac flights resume in four hours. As always, counseling services are available if you need them."
