8402, "(fr)STX Exploration Fabrication"
8403, "(fr)STX Exploration Processor"
8404, "(fr)!html We know that IN.E.D.A.M.01 has been constructing more drones, and we can only surmise some of them have deployed to reinforce the blockade in Laramis. Captain Jers has looked over the data, and decided to hold the line here at Amanu. We'll be up against the bulk of INEDAM's fleet, but the Second Dawn Society has a plan to even the odds. Director?"
8405, "(fr)!html Thank you, <span class='blue'>Captain<$slashspan>. INEDAM hit Kalvis Station about thirty hours ago. That station manufactured weapons for the LNA fighter corps, and what's left remains under INEDAM's control. When the LNA tried to retake it, INEDAM deployed a minefield around the ammo depot. They plan to hit us with our own weapons, and we're going to turn the tables.

We know INEDAM operates at least two variants of these mines - the low-yield, independently-mobile variant you encountered in Laramis, and the standard fixed version the LNA has had to contend with. Critically, these mines were deployed from a Morgens gunship. That means they're the high-yield variant, and it also means they can't easily retreat."
8406, "(fr)Ammo Depot"
8407, "(fr)!html IN.E.D.A.M.01 has already departed the op site, and no other warships are currently present. This gives us a window of opportunity. The LNAsc Shen Kuo will deploy to Kalvis in advance. My engineers have developed a probe capable of relaying her viral weapons, which she'll seed throughout the depot. Without a Ker-Ahes on site to block it, the INEDAM drones will be limited to their onboard AI. Enough of the depot has been cleared out for it to be a low-value target, so the INEDAM drones shouldn't be too interested in what we're up to. That's good, because we're going to steal enough mines to cripple IN.E.D.A.M.01's drone bay."
8408, "(fr)!html When the Shen Kuo gives the all-clear, the Izanami will deploy to Kalvis with a complement of five Hegias utility drones. Alpha, my engineers have cooked up an application for you to boss the drones around. When you're in the field, run <span class='white'>OSPREY ACTIVATE<$slashspan> in your terminal. It will let you collect data about a mine's expected yield and flag high-yield mines for capture. We need a total yield of <span class='white'>1200<$slashspan>, but more is always welcome.

Stay clear of INEDAM assets if at all possible. The more we provoke them, the more likely they are to see through the Shen Kuo's IWAR. We can all imagine how a dogfight in a minefield would end up. The Shen Kuo will keep tabs on INEDAM comm traffic. If those numbers spike, pull back."
8409, "(fr)Hegias Drones"
8410, "(fr)!html I don't want to be the kind of billionaire who wastes their time putting cars into space. I'll be on the Izanami to personally oversee this operation. Try not to get me killed out there. Remember, <span class='white'>OSPREY ACTIVATE<$slashspan>, then follow the prompts. Get a total yield of 1200, and don't poke the bear if you can help it.

Anything I missed?


That's everything. Alpha, get suited up."
8411, "(fr)!html Welcome back, pilots. Well done. You captured all the mines we needed to make our plan work. I know this wasn't the most exciting of operations, but this will be critical to our defense of Amanu. Director Ekul sends their thanks for keeping an eye out for the Izanami as well."
8412, "(fr)!html Welcome back, pilots. You captured seventy-five percent the mines we needed to make our plan work. It's not everything we hoped for, but I'm told we can make it work. I know this wasn't the most exciting of operations, but this will be critical to our defense of Amanu. Director Ekul sends their thanks for keeping an eye out for the Izanami as well."
8413, "(fr)!html Pilots, you were only able to capture fifty percent of what we needed to make our defense plan work. I hate to bring you bad news this way, but I'm told there is no chance we can fend off IN.E.D.A.M.01 with this. The officers are scrambling. We expected better of you, pilot."
8414, "(fr)!html Pilots, you were only able to capture twenty-five percent of what we needed to make our defense plan work. I hate to bring you bad news this way, but I'm told there is no chance we can fend off IN.E.D.A.M.01 with this. The officers are scrambling. We expected better of you, pilot."
8415, "(fr)!html In fact, you captured every single mine out there. You've got more patience than I do. Ekul says they're not sure what she'll do with the leftovers, but knowing the SDS, I bet they'll come up with something."
8416, "(fr)!html However, you also alerted the INEDAM to your presence. It's likely they may have guessed what we're up to. Because of that we expect the assault on Amanu to be increased. The INEDAM AI won't want to take any chances. This could be a major setback."
8417, "(fr)!html We've got two days until IN.E.D.A.M.01's expected arrival at Amanu. Get some rest. You're gonna need it."
