8543, "(fr)!html <div class='blue'>Amanu Station<br$slash>Luyten System<br$slash>2342/06/14<$slashdiv>

<span class='blue'>Amanu's logistical situation<$slashspan>

Your attention, everyone. We've got a lot to get through, none of it good. As we'd feared, Amanu Station's hydroponics are struggling to keep up with the increased strain. The LNA has been unable to recover any equipment from the bio stations over Luyten I after INEDAM's latest attack. Unless we can find a way through the node blockades or the LNA can work something out with their hydroponics, we have no choice but to continue with emergency rationing.

The Elcano-class habitats <span class='blue'>Whiskey<$slashspan> and <span class='blue'>Lima<$slashspan> are currently moving to the Oort Cloud. The SDS has several smaller outposts in the region that have yet to see any INEDAM activity, and the hope is that the bulk of our population will be secure there for a few more weeks at least. Habitat <span class='blue'>Bravo<$slashspan> suffered a drive failure after an INEDAM attack two days ago, and can't currently make the jump, so it's here at Amanu for the time being.

Lastly, the STX mining facility has become too much of a liability to defend, and personnel on board made the decision to abandon the facility. It became INEDAM scrap about two hours ago, not long after evac was completed. <span class='blue'>Habitat Bravo<$slashspan> has some capacity left, but not enough for everyone, so get comfy - you'll have a few more roommates moving in over the next couple hours."
8544, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>INEDAM's progress<$slashspan>

I'm aware none of that is welcome news, and I'm afraid the update on IN.E.D.A.M.01's progress is just as grim. Thirty minutes ago, the INEDAM fleet destroyed the last STX mining station orbiting Luyten II. The only thing between the fleet and us here at Amanu is the refueling site at <span class='yellow'>BL-UV L5<$slashspan>. Projections put IN.E.D.A.M.01's arrival at eight hours plus or minus 20 minutes. We must hold the line here.

If there's one upside of INEDAM's rampage across the system, it's that we've made good use of our time here at Amanu. If IN.E.D.A.M.01 brings its fleet to bear on this station, we're more than ready to retaliate in kind. Between our own warships and the PVN's, the LNA's beam cutters, and Tyrving platforms supplied by the SDS, it is my professional opinion that we have the firepower to repel this attack and turn INEDAM's own momentum against it. In the end, it all comes down to good flying.

You have four hours. Eat, rest, and do whatever you need to prepare for what's coming. We need everyone at their absolute best. Frag briefings start at 2115, and I expect every ship in the air by 2200. You'll liaise with Director Abe of Amanu's air wing while I coordinate with our cruiser elements. If you need stims from medbay, now's the time."
8545, "(fr)!html <span class='blue'>New Technology: Ion Torch<$slashspan>

One last note. Recovery of equipment from the STX refinery has allowed the LNA to devise an experimental piece of fighter equipment. The Ion Torch is highly unconventional, combining aspects of a weapon and a maneuvering thruster. Firing the weapon will knock your fighter into reverse at high speeds, making it an effective option for opening the distance in a dogfight, or so the test pilots claim."
8546, "(fr)!html Pilots, let's get through this quickly so you can choose your loadouts and get in the air. LNA recon flights have reported a buildup of INEDAM ships around the command carrier. It's coming right on schedule, and we're ready for it. Those of you who were involved with the little heist at Luyten I may know where this is going.

We expect IN.E.D.A.M.01 to throw everything it can at the station, and we've arranged overlapping defensive lines to dull the force of its attack. Amanu Station has no on board turrets, but is protected by a series of eight flak cannon sentries. These are now supplemented by two artillery platforms courtesy of the Second Dawn Society. When the attack begins, the Harewood, Marion, Nubia, Chicxulub, and Duamutef will take up positions within the sentry screen. The GTA's&nbsp$semicolonCaptain Jers has tactical authority over these units' formation. The SDS Izanami and our own Ifrit will form a second line of defense. Their missile launchers have performance comparable to the GTA Siren missile and an effective range of just under a klick. Dr. Sarno's&nbsp$semicolonLavoisier will provide holographic support. After his performance at Wayfarer Station, Elias Pendergast has volunteered the Opportunity for search-and-rescue. His gunners will do what they can to intercept torpedoes that make it past the flak screen."
