8778, "(fr)The HLC Taweret has come under attack.	A GTA strike mission scrambles to capture the ship first."
8779, "(fr)!html Listen up, because we're short on time. Five minutes ago, the Duamutef picked up an HoL distress call from the Taweret. It seems that they came under attack by IN.E.D.A.M.01 and were forced to withdraw. The message was heavily distorted, but we think it says that INEDAM drones boarded the Taweret during the fighting.

We presume that these are the same drones we encountered aboard the ICv Gallaecia, and likely its means of controlling the <span class='red italic'>Warshawski<$slashspan> and <span class='red italic'>Amber VI<$slashspan>. Fortunately, the Taweret's crew was able to drive them off, but IN.E.D.A.M.01 is still in hot pursuit."
8780, "(fr)!html This presents us with a golden opportunity. The Taweret's ability to use Lascaux devices makes it the only ship capable of bypassing the INEDAM blockade. As such, this is both a rescue and a capture operation. You must protect the Taweret from INEDAM's attack until we can secure the ship for our own purposes.

Once the Taweret is under our control, we will bring up the ship's convergence engine and link up with a Lascaux artifact in GTA space. Maintain your escort of the Taweret until she departs. At that point, we expect INEDAM to retaliate, so you will immediately return to Amanu Station and assist in defense."
8781, "(fr)Allied System"
8782, "(fr)!html The odds are not on our side here. It took everything we had to stop IN.E.D.A.M.01 at the <span class='white'>Battle of Amanu<$slashspan>, and we don't have enough assets available to mount an effective assault. So we're opting for more of a surgical strike.

Once Alpha begins their capture operation, the rest of the 508th will launch in Zeus bombers with Stiletto missiles. Bêta, you will harass IN.E.D.A.M.01 to keep it away from Alpha while they disable and then protect the cruiser. Alpha, avoid engaging any INEDAM forces unless you absolutely have to."
8783, "(fr)!html Once the Taweret is disabled, we will send in capture teams and engineers. They'll be lead by the <span class='green italic'>HLT Qetesh<$slashspan> with the Duamutef's Marines aboard. Their familiarity with HoL systems will be invaluable, and if they were going to double-cross us, they'd have done so by now. Keep them alive until they've landed.

We expect INEDAM to have worked out what's going on by this point, and it's entirely possible the HoL loyalists will try to deny us the Taweret. Protect it from any and all threats until its ready to depart."
8784, "(fr)Qetesh"
8785, "(fr)!html We're down to our last card here. We don't have the strength left to stand against IN.E.D.A.M.01 again, and if we can't contact GTA Command, then we're truly at the mercy of a rogue AI. Check your loadouts and launch as soon as you're ready."
8786, "(fr)!html The HLC Taweret escaped the system, taking our chance of contacting Terran Command with it. It's only a matter of time before INEDAM returns to Amanu, and we're all out of tricks."
8787, "(fr)!html The HLC Taweret was destroyed during our capture operation, taking our chance of contacting Terran Command with it. It's only a matter of time before INEDAM returns to Amanu, and we're all out of tricks."
8788, "(fr)!html Captain Jers has ordered a full evacuation of the system. Our only option at this point is to force our way through the Laramis node and hope some ships make it through. One way or the other, Terran colonization of Luyten is at its end."
