9095, "(fr)!html Welcome to the GTD Delacroix, Commander. I'm sure it's not every day you get debriefed by a flag officer, but we find ourselves in interesting times. I've been authorized to inform you that the Joint Chiefs of Staff and a <span class='blue'>Congressional<$slashspan> delegation are assembling in Delta Serpentis to receive your squadron's testimony. This is a highly sensitive situation, Commander, but it also represents an opportunity for you. It's not every fighter jock who gets to advise the highest military and civilian authorities in our chain of command. Think carefully about the optics of the situation, and this just might work out very well for you. That is my personal advice, Commander. The big-picture reality of the situation is rather more grim.

I've also been authorized - ah, thank you, Lieutenant. Coffee, Commander? It's my own personal supply, imported from Procyon. There's cream and sugar here if you'd like either.

I've also been authorized to inform you of the situation in Luyten. Following the declaration of <span class='white'>Case Apollyon<$slashspan>, Allied and Imperial forces throughout known space entered a state of heightened readiness, and were able to deploy as details came through. The PVD Ranger arrived from Ross 128, followed by shortly by the GTD Minnow, GTD Uhuru, PVD Hedetet, and their battlegroups. Apparently, these... INEDAM drones struggled to mount a coordinated response without their command ship. Humanitarian efforts are ongoing, while the Vasudan forces have established a blockade around the alien FTL artifact. Acting Captain Jers sends her regards.

That brings us to the situation behind us in Adhara. A lot of people died in the fighting, Commander. Adhara's biosphere was also damaged, and the planetary government is already assembling a task force to prevent total collapse. Politically, the fallout is going to be even worse than Antarès. Voices within the <span class='blue'>High Parliament of Adhara<$slashspan> are raising complaints at the highest levels. Some are even making secession noises, and, worryingly, Admiral Shirazi on the Malendroke has yet to release a statement. Until you receive guidance from <span class='blue'>Command<$slashspan>, <span class='white'>avoid doing or saying anything that may inflame the situation<$slashspan>. Your wingmate's statement on open comms is problematic enough.

My staff have filled me in on your report from Luyten. I also understand that Lieutenant Alex McPherson was killed in action during your retreat from Wayfarer Station. This is the second time my family have given their lives for this Alliance, Commander. It's news no husband or father ever wants to hear. I only wish he could know how proud he made me. We all swore the same oath. We have the same duty to the GTA and her people. When you're there in that <span class='blue'>Congressional<$slashspan> hearing, I hope you'll do the right thing."
9096, "(fr)!html Thank you for joining me, pilots. The Malendroke has been providing security in Adhara for the past three years. Catching the system's ultra-elite pushing illegal cargo is typically what passes for action out here. I like to think we gave those drones a decent showing, but I won't pretend we had the firepower to stop them ourselves. Of course, if it weren't for you they wouldn't be here, but you could say the same about GTI building the damn things in the first place. Yes, I heard what Alpha 2 said on the ascent, and I concur with their assessment. The Joint Chiefs of Staff are convening in Delta Serpentis as we speak. They're going to try to cover this up. They're going to interview you, and when the time comes, I hope you'll remember your oaths to the letter.

I've seen the latest numbers from <span class='blue'>Vandenberg<$slashspan>. They're predicting between ten and twenty thousand casualties and <span class='white'>irreparable<$slashspan> damage to the biosphere. Enough of the weather control network remains intact that we should be able to stave off total collapse, but it's not a guarantee. <span class='blue'>Command<$slashspan>, in their infinite wisdom, wants to recall the Malendroke for debriefing. I have politely informed them that our medical and logistical facilities aren't going anywhere, so you'll be going home on the GTFr Jakarta once she's finished onboarding patients.

I do have some good news for you, at least. Concurrently with our engagement of the IN.E.D.A.M.01 carrier, the PVD Ranger, GTD Minnow, GTD Uhuru, and PVD Hedetet transited the Luyten node and proceeded to wipe the floor with the drones still in system. The Hedetet's battlegroup has assumed blockade positions around the alien artifact while the rest of the fleet provides logistical support. Speaking of which, expect a political fight about control of the remains of the Adhara artifact.

Pilots, I've brought myself up to speed on your data from Luyten. You've been through hell and back, and I wish I could say this was the end. I maintain a close working relationship with the <span class='blue'>High Parliament of Adhara<$slashspan>, and I've received word that they plan to issue a statement demanding accountability and redress from the Alliance. I do not intend to condemn this statement. The people of Adhara are furious, and I fear there may be more bloodshed in the future. When you're there in that <span class='blue'>Congressional<$slashspan> hearing, I hope you'll do the right thing."
