9143, "(fr)It's about to jump! Command?!"
9144, "(fr)EMP, EMP! Shit, I've lost control!"
9145, "(fr)Alpha 2 to Command! Mayday! I'm in an uncontrolled descent, request immediate evac!"
9146, "(fr)Pilots, your transmission is jumbled, do not copy. Say again, do not copy."
9147, "(fr)All friendlies are deadstick, Command! Engine avionics inoperable! We are in an uncontrolled ballistic descent!"
9148, "(fr)Sensors are clearing up. Stay calm, everyone, we see you. Standby."
9149, "(fr)Stand by for what?! That ship's about to jump! Even if we could reset in time we'll never clear the blowback!"
9150, "(fr)If we should die tonight..."
9151, "(fr)Always knew this hero thing was a bad idea. Smoke if you... hey, radar's coming back. The hell..."
9152, "(fr)Malendroke and Delacroix, priority alert! Hold fire! Catastrophic hull failure in progress on IN.E.D.A.M.01!"
9153, "(fr)Solid copy. Guns, cease action!"
9154, "(fr)That's for Wayfarer!"
9155, "(fr)Pilots, prepare for incoming debris. Destroyers, can you reach Vandenberg?"
9156, "(fr)They're aware of the situation. Shirazi's gunners worked out a firing solution to mitigate surface damage. The worst of the debris should burn up or splash down in a lake."
9157, "(fr)Admiral, this is Vandenberg. The remaining drones are... weird. It's like they're drunk, but they're not inert. And we've got a lot of wounded with debris still impacting the surface. Could we get some help down here?"
9158, "(fr)We're dispatching all available transports and a wing of reinforcements to handle the drones."
9159, "(fr)Well, Mav, we did it. Fate in a missile."
9160, "(fr)Delacroix, the area is secure and fuel levels are joker. We're bugging out."
9161, "(fr)Copy, Epsilon. Pilots, your RTB is authorized. Transmitting autopilot trajectory now."
9162, "(fr)Still hate this part."
9163, "(fr)Strike force, Malendroke Actual. I've reviewed your data dump about the INEDAM threat a dozen times over. I appreciate the tactical precis, but now that the immediate crisis is over, I would like some strategic information. Where did that ship come from?"
9164, "(fr)GTI, Admiral. It started as an anti-Vasudan wunderweapon. After the war, they kept it under wraps until they lost control after Hades."
9165, "(fr)I... Understood, Alpha."
9166, "(fr)Sir, not that I disagree... Might High Command have preferred a more confidential disclosure?"
9167, "(fr)Have you ever wondered how I got assigned here? Why's a big bad undercover agent flying patrols off Centaur Station? I'm sure you've wondered."
9168, "(fr)Hey, everyone's got a story. Not my place to pry."
9169, "(fr)It's a story, alright. During the Hades Rebellion, I risked OpSec to bail out a PVN refugee convoy. My unit still managed to complete our objectives, just with a couple hundred more Vasudan civilians alive. The Alliance had me court-martialed for insubordination."
9170, "(fr)Ever since then, I told myself I'd get back in their good graces some day. Then this happened. I'm sure the Malendroke and Delacroix did everything they could, but that's still hundreds of kilos of debris headed toward the surface."
9171, "(fr)Three hundred thousand people at the landing site. Probably half as many at the other surface settlements. Thousands more on the orbitals. If the Alliance's dirty laundry is putting civilian lives at stake, I don't see how my oath lets me not air it."
9172, "(fr)That's, uh... What if they court martial you again? I mean, would they, you know..."
9173, "(fr)I'm not aware of any official classification level on that information. Are you?"
9174, "(fr)Guess not."
9175, "(fr)Susan, what're we going to do?"
9176, "(fr)We signed on when the AF announced their treaty with Holly. As long as they're still out there, there's still a fight worth fighting."
9177, "(fr)Ever thought about going back to private security? I, uh, I know a pilot coming off a stint with the military, maybe looking for something to do with his life. Or, hell, maybe the LNA'll take me."
9178, "(fr)Wasn't there a $quotePookie$quote waiting for you?"
9179, "(fr)Uh... He's a teddy bear."
9180, "(fr)Pilots, we have recalled transports from across the system to help evacuate the wounded. Your autopilot trajectory should maintain a safe distance."
9181, "(fr)Copy, Malendroke."
9182, "(fr)Delacroix to the 508th. I'd like to know if you can answer a question of a personal nature."
9183, "(fr)Hells. Let me take this."
9184, "(fr)Affirmative, Delacroix. I think the autopilot can handle flying in a straight line."
9185, "(fr)Thank you, pilots. I don't read Lieutenant McPherson's fighter among your formation. Is he in Luyten?"
9186, "(fr)Before our last sortie together... Mav told me he wanted to be someone you'd be proud of, sir. And then our station came under attack. He stayed behind to get the last of our pods out. He singlehandedly saved our entire command roster. None of us would be here without him."
9187, "(fr)Guy was a terrible card player and a real stick-in-the-mud when he wanted to be, but I'm gonna miss him. That ain't something I can say about most folk. Uh, sir."
9188, "(fr)Thank you, pilots."
9189, "(fr)Delacroix, during your transit, did you encounter a Wyvern transport named Opportunity?"
9190, "(fr)Affirmative. They raised us in Epsilon Pegasi, even before Admiral Shirazi's transmission got through. It's not every day a civilian calls Apollyon. I assume that was your doing?"
9191, "(fr)Guilty as charged, Admiral. What was their status? Our position in Luyten needs reinforcements."
9192, "(fr)Once the dust settles, you'll have to tell me how you ended up here to get reinforcements there."
9193, "(fr)It's a long story, sir. We're nearing the mesopause, and I'll feel a lot more comfortable once we're out of atmo."
9194, "(fr)Understood, Alpha. The Opportunity reported an ETA of thirty minutes. We left her as she was jumping to Vega. Our hangar is green to receive you."
9195, "(fr)Advisory, we are setting up to approach the Delacroix's hangar. Please hold position."
9196, "(fr)Yes, 508th, hold position. Call for refuel if you need to. This might be a moment."
9197, "(fr)Admiral Shirazi, stand down. These pilots have critical information for High Command."
9198, "(fr)And I've got a system that just went to hell. Terran Command can wait a few hours. They'll need that time to even assemble the JCOS."
9199, "(fr)Pardon me, is there a problem?"
9200, "(fr)Just a jurisdictional matter, pilot. Shirazi, we don't know whether this threat has been fully contained."
9201, "(fr)We do know there are now-uncontrolled drones in this system. Alpha, Bêta, you're cleared to land."
9202, "(fr)Belay that! 508th, your oath is to the GTA, not Adhara. We need to debrief you ASAP."
9203, "(fr)You're making a mistake, Admiral."
9204, "(fr)Uh, never thought I'd say this, but... anyone else miss INEDAM?"
9205, "(fr)I mean, she's right. She's obviously right."
9206, "(fr)If you think that factors into fleet politics... It's a complicated situation, Hermes."
9207, "(fr)Boss, we've been through hell together. I'll follow your lead."
9208, "(fr)Heh... Sorry, One."
9209, "(fr)Thank you, pilots. Malendroke, I'll make sure you're kept in the loop. Helm, set course for the Epsilon Pegasi node."
