942, "(fr)Cargo Platform"
943, "(fr)Cargo platforms are limited-capacity stationary docking platforms for cargo containers. A typical cargo platform has a slightly magnetized hull, allowing workers to access the cargo without complex zero-G maneuvers. Many also boast networked security systems, providing a warning if a container is accessed unexpectedly, and some platforms have station-keeping thrusters to avoid drifting from their assigned position."
944, "(fr)Model 3 Gas Ring"
945, "(fr)The Subach-Innes Model 3 Gas Distribution Ring is a facility for the storage of refined volatile gases in atmospheric conditions, generally those of the gas giants from which they were harvested. The device can be fitted with a variety of modifications, including small engines for atmospheric altitude stabilization and filtration kits, which allow very basic refinement and elimination of gross impurities, though they are not substitutes for a full refinery."
