10597, "(fr)The Somnambulist is an old class of explorer ship, designed by Nankam Aeronautical on behalf of Ambrosia Logistical Solutions. The lead ship of the class, also designated Somnambulist, launched on a celebrated mission into the distant N362 system, which is known for highly energetic subspace phenomena. Her sister ship, the Carter, was similarly celebrated, and competition for berths was high. The Carter mission discovered a new class of subspace anomaly in Luyten. Unfortunately for the crew and scientific minds aboard, it did so by running into one, throwing the ship through the subspace barrier and causing considerable hull stress in the process. As if to rub salt in the wound, it was later found that the Elcano-class explorer, which had competed for the contract with the Somnambulist, would have been able to detect and avoid the anomaly, and ultimate responsibility for the wreck was placed on cost-cutting measures at Nankam. After correcting these flaws in the third and final Somnambulist, the Kuranes, and retrofitting the original ship to the same standards, Nankam managed to redeem itself, and both ships remained active with Ambrosia's scientific arm until they were outmoded by the smaller, more versatile Faustus years later."
