4668, "(fr)THANUT: This large, cold, rocky world hosts a population of seven million Terrans and 44 million Vasudans, living in expensive, climate-controlled underground cities. Much of its Vasudan population originally settled in Antarès as part of a massive PVN land grab during the early years of the Terran-Vasudan War, only for the system to be fully recaptured by the Terrans in 2327. Thanut's political and economic prestige are second only to Gulnara, thanks to its population, mining industry, and many civilian orbitals, though the loss of Sol has halted further sub-surface and orbital construction. After the Great War, it was judged to be a politically-expedient dumping ground for postwar refugees. Thanks to the construction freeze, much of the largely-Vasudan refugee population currently ekes out a subsistence-level existence in a number of ad-hoc orbital refugee camps.\n\nA cargo convoy delivering badly-needed supplies to Camp Angel and other orbital refugee camps disappeared at 0710 hours yesterday. GTI is still uncertain whether the convoy was attacked by smugglers, the HoL, or both."
4667, "(fr)UMBALA: An icy, resource-poor world, with a population of 2.3 million in underground colonies. Many 'net rumors still surround the loss of the military transport GTFr Fitzgerald in the low planetary orbit in 2330.\n\nWhile the Intrépide is out of system, Admiral Po has ordered Operation CENTER, a full sweep of Umbala and its orbit for smuggler and HoL bases. CENTER has yet to turn up any hostile contacts."
4670, "(fr)ABONDAN: The outermost planet of the Antarès system, known to locals as 'Empty Eight'. Abondan was once the center of the system's gas-mining industry during the 2310s-2320s, until its reserves of useful gases were bled dry by the exigencies of Terran-Vasudan War. Now, it only hosts a few derelict orbitals, a shadow of its former economic importance."
4671, "(fr)BL CETI: BL Ceti, nicknamed Bora, is an intrinsic flare star of variable diameter and luminosity. Compared to the more notorious UV Ceti, BL Ceti is a comparatively unremarkable red dwarf, with an orbital period of roughly 26.5 years around the stars' shared barycenter. The influence of BL Ceti on Luyten is significant, as it serves to mediate the intense, unpredictable radiation of its larger partner. Habitats employ the Lagrange points of Bora as a 'sun shield' against flares, although the complexities of orbital mechanics make this a complex task. Magnetoplasma storms curved around the gravity well of BL Ceti are a favored spot for antimatter collectors."
4672, "(fr)BL CETI AND UV CETI: The binary stars of the Luyten system. Both stars are flare variant red dwarfs with unusually intense even by the standards of flare stars. This radiation, unique to Luyten, requires all ships and stations to mount heavy shielding to protect inhabitants and electronics. The two stars are often nicknamed the Hellstars for their hellish impact on all colonists and researchers in Luyten."
4673, "(fr)BARBARY PLATFORM: This hidden smuggler depot used to be a trafficking point for rare and valuable illegal goods, and a center of the Antarès black market. Fighters from the GTD Intrépide, pursuing pirate vessels which had taken part in the recent attack on Antarès Station, discovered the depot and shut it down."
4674, "(fr)BENTLEY GAS STORAGE: A storage platform which holds raw gas canisters mined from New Oceania's atmosphere, until they can be refined by Koros and Sandomierz stations.\n\nHoL forces attacked Bentley Gas Storage while most nearby GTA units were busy defending Antarès Station and incoming convoys, knocking Bentley out of service until further notice."
4675, "(fr)BIO STATION FOUR: Bio Station Four's research aims to optimize food production throughout the LNA's habitats. Through the use of programmed molecular 'robots,' the LNA scientists working at Bio Station Four hope to maximize the effectiveness of their fertilizers in transferring nutrients to plants grown orbitally in hydroponic bays, significantly increasing crop yields and, by extension, Luyten's capacity for immigration. Like many LNA research products, Bio Station Four's fertilizers are also intended for export, since they'll be just as useful on a warship or deep-space explorer."
4676, "(fr)BIO STATION ONE: One of the older LNA research stations, Bio Station One was established as a sally point for probes studying the extremophile microbes on Luyten I's surface. While these missions still happen from time to time, the difficulty in keeping probes intact in the planet's noxious atmosphere has largely curtailed them, and Bio Station One has transitioned to more of an administrative role, providing oversight of the other research stations orbiting the planet. There is some jurisdictional friction regarding whether Kalvis Station, which occupies a nearby orbital slot but conducts unrelated research, should fall under Bio Station One's purview."
4677, "(fr)BIO STATION THREE: Genetic engineered bacterial strains and algae are the focus on research at Bio Station Three, with a focus on creating more efficient oxygen recycling and waste disposal systems than current chemical-based systems. Algae created at Bio Station Three can quickly absorb carbon dioxide and emit oxygen at rates unlike organic algae once transplanted from Earth, and bacteria can reduce waste products to a biologically inert sludge for ease of incineration. A secondary project focuses on next-gen survival rations, and has recently prototyped a calorically dense gelatin which remains edible nearly indefinitely and while readily accepting a wide range of flavoring agents. Researches from both projects promise they have not shared any notes."
4678, "(fr)BIO STATION TWO: Bio Station Two's research focuses on the implementation of post-CRISPR gene therapy to reverse radiation damage. Because of excessive exposure to waves of radiation generated by the Luyten stars, DNA degradation and resulting medical problems are a constant concern throughout the system. The scientists assigned to Bio Station Two are close to developing what is, in effect, an artificial retrovirus which can be customized with a sample of an individual's DNA, allowing it to detect and replace damaged strands before they can cause problems. In Luyten, ready access to this therapy would significantly lessen the convalescence period required after an EVA mission (or ejection), but it's also of considerable interest to reactor technicians across Terran space."
4679, "(fr)ANGEL REFUGE STATION: This ramshackle orbital camp, made of repurposed cargo containers, is home to 871 displaced refugees, 87% Vasudan and 13% Terran. Though Camp Angel was originally erected as a stopgap facility to house refugees from Vasuda during the Great War, the GTA government's overstretched financial and logistical situation makes it unlikely that its residents will find a permanent home anytime soon. Its inhabitants eke out a subsistence lifestyle in cramped conditions, fearful of being raided by smugglers, and distrustful of federal and system governments which have neglected them."
4680, "(fr)CLYDESDALE WEATHER STATION: Built in late 2334 to manage Hesperia's weather patterns, Clydesdale Station plays a key role in the ongoing and successful terraforming efforts on Hesperia."
4681, "(fr)DASHNELL PILOTS' ACADEMY: This military station is the main training center for the Antarès System Guard's pilot corps. It was named after a local hero who died in the Battle of Talania during the Terran-Vasudan War.\n\nDashnell's graduating class has been deployed early to active duty, to supplement Antarès's overstretched fighter corps. Pilot morale is high after the Antarian repulse of the attack on Hillross Station."
4682, "(fr)DECOMMISSIONED WEATHER STATION: The solar monitoring station in orbit of Luyten II was the earliest human construction built in the Luyten system. It was intended to monitor coronal mass ejection cycles from UV Ceti to determine the possibility of establishing a permanent research station. Within a year of the station's construction, solar radiation had degraded the weather platform's sensors to the point where it could no longer report meaningful data, and the project was quietly shelved. What data was received, however, proved highly valuable, and lead to the development of new forms of radiation shielding, paving the way for STX Exploration and eventually the LNA to move in. The weather station no longer serves any practical function, but has been left intact out of historical interest."
4683, "(fr)DETIULA STATION: An abandoned military outpost, constructed to guard the Vasuda node at one of Antarès's Lagrange points in 2328, when Antarès was a frontline system in the Terran-Vasudan War. After the Great War, the GTA government could no longer afford to maintain two large and outdated fortifications deep within Terran-Vasudan borders, and abandoned the station."
4684, "(fr)DJOSER STATION: Originally erected as a military supply base during the Vasudan invasion of Antarès in 2324, Djoser Station is now Antarès's most prominent Vasudan civilian habitat and trade hub. Its holding capacity and docking facilities have been taxed to their limit by the recent influx of refugees from Vasuda Prime."
4685, "(fr)DOCEITOV CLOUD: An anomaly that defies any explanation, the Doceitov Cloud is a dense collection of what by all means should be nebular gases, intermixed with an unusual high density of metallic particles. Ordinarily, the Cloud's density would have been high enough for it to have long since collapsed into its own gravity well, but a number of intermittent radiation sources have been detected at the Cloud's center whose radiation pressure narrowly overcomes the Cloud's gravity and keeps it stable. Tantalizingly, these radiation sources' periodic nature and emission spectra are consistent with Rosenthal-Albertsen Bypass Objects, or RABOs, a proposed but unproven type of subspace effect of immense theoretical interest. Unfortunately, the Cloud is an unforgiving place. While the outer layer can be traversed relatively safely, radiation, energized plasma, electromagnetic storms, and even lightning carried by the Cloud's metallic particles are all common closer to the core, and it is currently believed that a vessel capable of making the journey safely would rival an Orion-class fleet carrier in scale. For now, the LNA contents itself with surveys of the relatively safe outer levels."
4686, "(fr)EPHESOS STATION: Ephesos Station is described by the Second Dawn Society as an 'arsenal station'. Like other SDS installations, the majority of the station's structure is inside a large Oort Cloud object. Most of the asteroid's internal volume has been converted into a dizzying array of drone hangars, capable of housing and deploying Peregrine and Elepaio sensor probes, Phidias and Hegias utility drones, and even Amazon Advanced training drones modified as subspace-capable carriers for smaller drone types. Ephesos' primary role in a Shivan survival scenario will be to discreetly monitor their movements with its probes, allowing the SDS to coordinate efforts and remain undetected. For now, Ephesos is primarily employed as a construction depot, using its drones to set up infrastructure and booby traps throughout the Oort Cloud. The 'arsenal' in 'arsenal station' comes from a stock of explosive-laden Amazons being developed as crude subspace-capable torpedoes, which were unfortunately confiscated by the Hammer of Light during their occupancy of Megiddo Station."
4687, "(fr)EXXON-BECKHAM REFINERY 204: One of the refineries which process the raw gas harvested from Esperanza."
4688, "(fr)EXXON-BECKHAM REFINERY 207: One of the refineries which process the raw gas harvested from Esperanza."
4689, "(fr)EXXON-BECKHAM REFINERY 307: A derelict gas refinery, abandoned after Abondan's rare gas pockets were drained dry by intense harvesting during the Terran-Vasudan War."
4690, "(fr)EXXON-BECKHAM REFINERY 308: A derelict gas refinery, abandoned after Abondan's rare gas pockets were drained dry by intense harvesting during the Terran-Vasudan War."
4691, "(fr)EXXON-BECKHAM STORAGE 252: A storage platform which holds raw gas canisters until they can be refined by one of Exxon-Beckham's 12 gas refineries orbiting Esperanza."
4692, "(fr)The Somnambulist is an old class of explorer ship, designed by Nankam Aeronautical for GTA expeditions. The lead ship of the class, also designated Somnambulist, launched on a celebrated mission into the distant N362 system, which is known for highly energetic subspace phenomena. Her sister ship, the Carter, was similarly celebrated, and competition for berths was high. The Carter mission discovered a new class of subspace anomaly in Luyten. Unfortunately for the crew and scientific minds aboard, it did so by running into one, throwing the ship through the subspace barrier and causing considerable hull stress in the process. As if to rub salt in the wound, it was later found that the Elcano-class explorer, which had competed for the contract with the Somnambulist, would have been able to detect and avoid the anomaly, and ultimate responsibility for the wreck was placed on cost-cutting measures at Nankam. The Carter's wreck has been anchored to the anomaly as both a navigational marker and a reminder of the human cost of corporate greed."
4693, "(fr)GULNARA: The capital of the Antarès system, and home to over 70 million inhabitants. As the only terrestrial object within Antarès's habitable zone, Gulnara has been the most heavily-populated world in Antarès ever since the first Terran colonial efforts in 2302. New Shanghai, the planetary capital, is the center of Antarès government. Gulnara is a hotbed of Antarian particularist agitation against the GTA's recent policies.\n\nThe Antarès Federation, a pro-independence fringe group, has been steadily gaining mainstream support and endorsements on Gulnara."
4694, "(fr)GULNARA RESEARCH STATION: A private research station specializing in geological and historical studies."
4695, "(fr)."
4696, "(fr)HABITAT BRAVO: Of the Elcanos serving as habitats for the Luyten New Alliance, Habitat Bravo is in the worst state of repair, having been originally decommissioned due to a severe asteroid strike long before her transfer to the LNA. Despite occasional system failures, the scientists and workers on Habitat Bravo have maintained and repaired the vessel to mostly operational condition, and the ship itself has served as a demonstration of many successful technologies created by LNA scientists. The habitat's designation comes from the jump node to Barnard's Star, which it follows around."
4697, "(fr)HABITAT LIMA: A repurposed Elcano colony ship. Habitat Lima has a population primarily of contracted scientists from a variety of smaller corporations, with a smaller proportion of independent scientists and infrastructure workers. Significant amounts of space on the station's lower decks are set aside as publicly available labs for ad-hoc experiments. The habitat's designation refers to the Laramis jump node, which it follows around. Of the three jump nodes in Luyten, only this node leads to GTA territory, and Habitat Lima is therefore kept in pristine condition, with two decks set aside for receiving out-of-system VIPs."
4698, "(fr)HABITAT WHISKEY: For better or for worse, Habitat Whiskey lives up to its name. The habitat's primary population includes work crews and miners, both LNA citizens and temporary residents, and the habitat has developed a $quotedowntown$quote reputation, a down-to-Earth place separate from the LNA's academic and governmental interests. The habitat's command staff have accepted the irregular arrangement, and have even made a modest profit through the sale of 'HW-Grade Whiskey' for the habitat's residents and visitors to enjoy. Less whimsically, the habitat is also the seat of the LNA's judicial branch and penal system."
4699, "(fr)HASTINGS DEPOT: A moderately-busy civilian hub in the outer reaches of the system, providing fueling and storage services to a number of small intra-system concerns. Hastings's deep-space isolation makes it an ideal place for smugglers to conduct business away from prying eyes, despite occasional customs inspections by the over-stretched Antarès security forces."
4700, "(fr)HESPERIA: This moon houses a booming subterranean colony of seven million Terran and Vasudan citizens. The success of recent ProGov-sponsored terraforming efforts has made Hesperia one of the few success stories in the grim economic picture of modern Antarès.\n\nMarines from the Intrépide Battlegroup raided a large Hesperia hab block on a Vasudan merchant's report of large-scale food smuggling. The raid failed to turn up any illegal activity, and attracted heavy criticism from Antarian citizens."
4701, "(fr)HILLROSS STATION: Exxon-Beckham Orbital Mining's headquarters in Antarès, Hillross Station was built to house high-level executives and oversee gas-mining operations throughout the system. It remains an important fixture of Antarès's gas-mining industry, despite the recent economic downturns."
4702, "(fr)INNER BELT: The innermost of Antarès's two asteroid belts. As it is resource-poor, it is largely ignored by miners and other commercial interests.\n\nA few commercial outposts have reported sighting Hammer of Light activity, but the Intrépide lacks the fighters to execute a full sweep of the belt for the HoL."
4703, "(fr)IRAKLION CORRIDOR: The corridor of solar winds between Antarès Major and Minor. It is hazardous to space travel, and the Antarès Bureau of Space Travel has closed it to civilian spaceflight."
4704, "(fr)JACQUELINE: The largest of Cintilante's three moons. Pre-Terran-Vasudan War plans for its large-scale colonization were sharply curtailed by the outbreak of war. Currently supports a small colony of 25,000 stubborn holdouts, who support themselves with hydroponic fruit farms.\n\nAntarès Federation irregulars have repulsed a major pirate attack on Jacqueline's hydroponics farms. In gratitude, Governor Smythe thanked the AF in a public address, calling them 'the only reliable defense for poor Antarians.'"
4705, "(fr)JEMISON STATION: Named after a 21st century astronaut and biologist, Jemison Station is the LNA's xenobiological and xenocultural center. The LNA movement resonated with very few Vasudans, who were largely uninterested in joining a Terran cultural movement, responding to Terran needs, and lead by Terran interests. A small number, however, were interested in the opportunity to build understanding between the common people of both civilizations, and Jemison Station was constructed to meet their needs. Vasudan culture emphasizes history, and many of the LNA's Ancient artifacts are also held aboard Jemison Station, the better to cooperate on research with Vasudan archaeologists. A plan to store Shivan specimens on the station, however, was deemed offensive, and Shivan research is now held on a small auxiliary station sharing Jemison's orbital slot."
4706, "(fr)JEWEL STATION: This multi-billion-credit orbital habitat is a vacation home for the elite of Antarès's elite. Senators, CEOs, and celebrities can bask in the beauty of Cintilante's shimmer storms from the comfort of the most luxurious facilities Antarian money can buy.\n\nAntarès Federation fighters have been spotted launching from Jewel Station, repulsing pirate and HoL attacks throughout the system, wherever GTA forces have been too stretched to assist."
4707, "(fr)KALVIS STATION: While considered a research station, Kalvis is somewhat the metaphorical black sheep owing to the explicitly military nature of its research. It was here that the Huracan racing ship was rebuilt into the Tyr interceptor, and where the Maiman beam cannon was first devised. One famous incident at Kalvis occurred during the initial demonstration of the Tyr. The demonstration units were expected to perform a simple patrol around the station, culminating with some basic maneuvers. Instead, Kalvis' crew arranged for the fighters to make a series of close fly-bys of the station, ending with a deep dive into the planetary gravity well. Flight crews were spared discipline largely due to the effect it had on GTA observers, who assumed it had been planned to impress them. A section of Kalvis Station is shared with STX Exploration, who make use of it to fulfill weapons contracts with the GTA."
4708, "(fr)KOROS REFINERY: One of the two major refineries which process the raw gas harvested from New Oceania."
4709, "(fr)LASCAUX: An automated station of unknown origin, given the provisional designation $quoteLascaux$quote, was discovered by the LNAct Chicxulub while investigating potential INEDAM energy signatures. Its construction is radically unlike any known Terran, Vasudan, Shivan, or Ancient artifact, and current theory holds that the Lascaux was created by a civilization previously unattested by GTA or PVN xenoarchaeological research. If so, we know even less about this civilization than we do about the Ancients, and must extrapolate from the HLC Taweret's use of this artifact. The Lascaux seems to, in some way, make convergence engine technology into a viable form of interstellar travel, suggesting this civilization's faster-than-light technology developed along a radically different path than our own. It is likely that they were destroyed by a Shivan incursion into their space, or in conflict with the Ancient empire."
4710, "(fr)LUYTEN I: In contrast to its cooler, irradiated twin, Luyten I has remained volcanically active for as long as Terrans have explored the system. The planet's surface has multiple active 'large igneous provinces', which have covered 37% of its crust with lava. This type of geological instability requires tremendous internal heat, and Luyten I is no exception. The planet's core is known to contain an unusually high density of radioisotopes, superheating the interior with their radioactive decay. The planet is also believed to have suffered a massive planetary impact in its (geologically) recent past, imparting further energy on the unstable world. Luyten I's volcanism is caught in a constant tug-of-war with UV Ceti, and the star's ionizing radiation strips away its thin atmosphere of toxic gas and ash as quickly as volcanic activity can replace it. No resources of note are believed to exist on the planet's surface, and no human has ever stepped foot on the world. All probes sent to perform basic geological surveys have expired within no later than 3 days of landing, with most either succumbing to atmospheric corrosion or breaking through the unstable crust into an underground lava flow. Bizarrely, multiple probes have confirmed the existence of microbial life, leading the LNA's biological research department to set up shop in orbit."
4711, "(fr)LUYTEN II: The second of Luyten's two planets is extremely rich in ore deposits, ranging from common minerals up to exotic heavy metals and radioisotopes. Exploiting this mineral wealth, however, is complicated by conditions on the planet's surface. Luyten II is tidally locked, with one face always facing UV Ceti, and constantly swept clean by extreme heat and coronal mass ejections. Only the most specialized of mining equipment can survive long enough to even recoup costs. The dark side, meanwhile, is locked up in a CO2-ice glacier, whose sheer scale and frigid temperatures complicate mining efforts. The LNA has recently transferred a wing of modified Tyr spacecraft to STX Exploration, carrying survey equipment and mining charges instead of weaponry, but still carrying their standard fighter shields, which have finally opened some of Luyten II's riches to Terran use. Curiously, the visible part of the planet's crust is marked by canyons and valleys consistent with surface erosion, suggesting that, before UV Ceti's transformation in 1957, it may have had a thicker atmosphere and liquid water."
4712, "(fr)MAHD: Port Zheng's sole moon, with a population of 0.8 million. Like its parent world, it is a mining center, whose economy has suffered from the post-Great War economic crash and smugglers' predations."
4713, "(fr)MARO HALO: The Maro Halo is a dense 'asteroid thicket' formed by the influence of a gravitational anomaly in Luyten's Oort Cloud. The anomaly is of scientific interest due to its similarity to the collapsed Sol jump node, although for it to have had warped the Oort Cloud as it has, it must be vastly older. The high density of asteroids in the Halo, meanwhile, makes it economically important as well. STX and LNA personnel frequently bump shoulders around the Halo, and have developed a friendly rivalry around their divergent objectives. On a more somber note, the gravitational anomaly complicates navigational calculations within the Halo, and ships operating in the Halo are required to reconfigure their jump drives to compensate."
4714, "(fr)MASADA STATION: An abandoned T-V War-era redoubt inside the Iraklion Corridor. Masada was constructed in 2326, as a bolthole for Terran forces if Antarès was lost to Vasudan advances. Like so many other Antarian stations, it was abandoned for budget reasons after the war. Its position inside the Corridor makes it very difficult to access."
4715, "(fr)MEGIDDO STATION: Megiddo Station is the headquarters of the ultra-survivalist Second Dawn Society, who intend to create a self-sustaining bastion that can outlast a second Shivan incursion. Built into a large Oort Cloud object with a highly eccentric orbit, the station has a minimal amount of superstructure on the surface of the asteroid, but protects itself from long-range sensors by keeping the majority of the structure buried inside. The interior of the station is highly utilitarian, with a majority of the usable area taken up by workshops, warehouses, life support systems, and the Society's well-equipped fighter corps."
4716, "(fr)MIDNIGHT: This small moon takes its name from its unusual orbital cycle, which keeps it in a state of near-perpetual eclipse. It is uninhabited."
4717, "(fr)MIDWINTER STATION: This bio-engineering facility, owned by Mensa Biotech, develops new engineered bacteria for use in planetary terraforming. The post-Great War need for living space has spurred new planetary colonization throughout Terran and Vasudan systems, and Mensa stands to profit handsomely from ProGov-sponsored Frontière colonial ventures."
4718, "(fr)MINERVA OUTPOST: A high-energy physics lab purpose-built by the LNA, Minerva is the only station of its type in existence. The station's core is a particle accelerator complex which the LNA uses for physics research. The extreme energy needs of Minerva's experiments would strain even the largest reactors in Allied space, so the LNA has devised an unusual solution. When power is needed for an experiment, a signal is sent to an antimatter pile a safe distance away, feeding a tightly focused X-ray laser which transfers power back to the accelerator. All ships jumping to Minerva are instructed to use a nearby navigational beacon and complete transit on standard drives, since a misjump while the beam is active could be catastrophic."
4719, "(fr)NOVOGRAD STATION: The sole military outpost in Antarès operated directly by the GTA federal government. Novograd was built to reinforce Detiula Station's defense of the Vasuda node in 2329, when Antarès was a frontline system in the Terran-Vasudan War. Positioned in one of the system's Lagrangian points, its presence earns it the resentment of Antarian particularist malcontents. Its four fighter squadrons are primarily tasked with overseeing traffic at the Vasuda jump node.\n\nDespite the Intrépide's arrival taking some pressure off Novograd's fighter wings, they still fly several sorties a day in support of Admiral Po's peacekeeping efforts."
4720, "(fr)NYUGEN-MESSIER WEATHER STATION: One of Gulnara's many orbitals, Nyugen-Messier plays a key role in managing the capital moon's weather patterns.\n\nSecurity fighters deployed by Megalith, a local PMC, disabled and destroyed the attacking HLC Herakleopolis as it attempted a kamikaze run on the station."
4721, "(fr)OORT CLOUD: At the furthest reaches of the Luyten system lies its unique Oort Cloud. This cloud of rocks, comets, and asteroids is unusually dense for a binary system. The cause for that density is unknown, but matter flares from UV Ceti cooling into a snowstorm of dust, boosting the mass density of the cloud over the centuries, is one speculative cause. The vital node to Laramis, and to the rest of known space, phases in and out of the field. One region of particular interest is the Maro Halo, a dense 'asteroid thicket' gradually collapsing towards a gravitational anomaly reminiscent of the one left behind by the collapsed Sol jump node, although for it to have had such an effect on the Oort Cloud, it must be vastly older. While the LNA conducts research of the anomaly, STX Exploration has a lucrative mining operation inside the Halo, using specially configured miners designed to tolerate the hazardous environment."
4722, "(fr)OUTER BELT: The outermost of Antarès's two asteroid belts. In 2331, during the Terran-Vasudan War it was the site of a running battle between the GTD Vienna and PVD Assurance."
4723, "(fr)PATMOS STATION: Long before the LNA was founded, Patmos Station was a civilian research lab studying the system's unusual stars. At some point during the 14 Years' War, the station was abandoned and purchased by Galactic Terran Intelligence for classified research of their own. After the defeat of the GTI Rebellion, the station was abandoned again, its personnel disappearing without a trace. The only record of their existence was an improvised radio telescope floating near the station, positioned to observe the Maro Halo anomaly in the system's Oort Cloud. Some believe Patmos's GTI crew joined up with the Second Dawn Society, though no evidence has ever surfaced to prove such, and the timeline is dubious as well."
4724, "(fr)REFINERY GLR04: An ore processor established by the Gerace Corporation, GLR04 and its siblings were set up to break up STX's near monopoly on Luyten's resources. Unfortunately, Gerace didn't have STX's expertise dealing with the environment of Luyten, and a few radiation-injury lawsuits later, they quickly abandoned the venture, selling off their Luyten infrastructure to STX at a loss. STX still operates these refineries in a limited capacity, aside from GLR04, which was ultimately purchased by the Second Dawn Society for their own purpose. It has since been moved to an undisclosed location in the Oort Cloud."
4725, "(fr)RIMCEE STATION: An orbital dock which handles metals traffic outbound from Port Zheng.\n\n\nRimcee has returned to full operation after the recent pirate attack. However, several extra-system companies have panicked and canceled metals orders from Port Zheng, despite Po deploying the GTC Nimrod to defend Port Zheng orbit."
4726, "(fr)ROTHENBERG-SINGH MINERAL REFINERY: Once state-of-the-art, this old station fell into disuse during the Fourteen Years War, and was subsequently stripped for parts by pre-LNA salvage gangs. It is no longer in use for its original purpose, but has found a new purpose - providing a safe place for LNA work crews to practice zero-G maneuvering. While new facilities for this purpose are on the LNA's agenda, there are currently no plans to decommission the Rothenberg-Singh platform, in part because many workers who've been educated aboard it feel a sort of affection for the old station."
4728, "(fr)STX EXPLORATION PROCESSOR: In operation for a decade and a half, this massive station is one of the few Namid-class installations in Terran space. Oort belt objects captured by STX mining expeditions are delivered to one of the station's processing bays to be broken up by magnetic accelerators and high explosives, liberating valuable metals and minerals for use elsewhere in the system. This processor is located near the Maro Halo, a large cluster of asteroids orbiting a minor gravitational anomaly. Mining operations here provide the majority of the LNA's supply of several essential materials."
4729, "(fr)STX EXPLORATION REFINERY: Raw material from STX's mining operations in Luyten are funneled to this station for initial refinement. Proprietary 'molecular forging' technology allows for extremely high extraction rates compared to conventional techniques. The technology was co-developed by STX and the LNA, and a small number of LNA technical observers can both be found here, responsible for ensuring everything goes smoothly as products are refined for export or further processing in STX's Aurora fabrication yard. It is legally unclear whether the LNA charter permits this sort of partnership without GTA involvement, but for now, the GTA has decided not to press the issue."
4730, "(fr)STX MINING FACILITY: This massive mining hub blurs the line between starship and installation. It is subspace-capable, but extremely slow, with a drive warmup time measured in hours. STX moves the facility only rarely, when too many of the economically useful asteroids in its vicinity have been exploited for it to remain profitable. The facility includes manipulator arms and mountings for asteroid-cracker explosives, and can process many of the more common mineral types by itself, while others are sent off to STX's Namid-class ore processor for further refinement."
4731, "(fr)STX PLANET MINING ONE: Two mining stations have been built by STX Exploration in low orbit of Luyten II. Both stations are equipped with Luyten-standard anti-radiation hull plating, but also mount experimental active radiation shield, or ARS, systems. Like fighter shields, the ARS is ultimately descended from Shivan shield technology. Unlike fighter shields, which much constantly protect the entire ship under battle conditions and so cannot scale up to protect warships or stations, the ARS is designed to activate only when ambient radiation crosses a trigger threshold, reinforcing the hull and helping dissipate the worst of the radiation surge. The LNA hopes that ARS modules will become a common feature on their habitats, increasing safety and reducing costs. In the mean time, STX uses the stations as sally point for mining shuttles, which dip down to the planet's surface and leave just as quickly."
4732, "(fr)STX PLANET MINING TWO: Two mining stations have been built by STX Exploration in low orbit of Luyten II. Both stations are equipped with Luyten-standard anti-radiation hull plating, but also mount experimental active radiation shield, or ARS, systems. Like fighter shields, the ARS is ultimately descended from Shivan shield technology. Unlike fighter shields, which much constantly protect the entire ship under battle conditions and so cannot scale up to protect warships or stations, the ARS is designed to activate only when ambient radiation crosses a trigger threshold, reinforcing the hull and helping dissipate the worst of the radiation surge. The LNA hopes that ARS modules will become a common feature on their habitats, increasing safety and reducing costs. In the mean time, STX uses the stations as sally point for mining shuttles, which dip down to the planet's surface and leave just as quickly."
4733, "(fr)SAN AUGUSTIN: The larger of Esperanza's two moons. A cold, lifeless, rocky ball, it is uninhabited by Terrans."
4734, "(fr)SAN FRANCISCO: The smaller of Esperanza's two moons. A cold, nigh-lifeless, rocky ball, inhabited only by a reclusive Catholic contemplative order of 25 monks."
4735, "(fr)SANDOMIERZ REFINERY: One of the two major refineries which process the raw gas harvested from New Oceania."
4736, "(fr)SARDIS STATION: Sardis Station is a highly unusual station operated by the Second Dawn Society. The station is built into a naturally hollow Oort Cloud object, and the SDS have put its massive inner chamber to a creative, albeit dangerous, use. A partially complete ship, the O-Inari, rests in Sardis' core. When complete, this ship will have the ability to jump from inside the station deep into UV Ceti's gravity well, deploy and retrieve portable antimatter condensers, and jump back to the station's interior, with the asteroid's bulk acting as a natural baffle to Shivan sensors. Should the Shivans return, this plan will provide the SDS with a reliable source of power so long as they can perform the extremely precise navigational calculations needed for the return journey."
4737, "(fr)SARPEDON: A cold ball of ice and rock, home only to automated mining industries."
4738, "(fr)SHAI: One of the three moons of Cintilante. Shai was the focus of a half-completed private terraforming project, canceled when the Terran-Vasudan war began in 2322."
4739, "(fr)SOUTH RADIO TELESCOPE: The second of four planned radio observatories operated by the LNA, situated in Luyten's ecliptic south, this automated telescope feeds astronomical data to scientists on Habitat Lima and throughout Luyten. Ever since the disappearance of its northern counterpart, the Southern Radio Telescope has been accompanied by a small flock of relay probes tied into Amanu Station's fast-response feed."
4740, "(fr)TARTARUS PENITENTIARY: The highest-security prison in Antarès, where the worst criminals in the system are locked up. The post-Great War crime wave of smuggling and piracy has stretched Tartarus's holding capacity to its limits, making its already-notorious conditions even worse."
4741, "(fr)THANATOS: This frozen ball of ice and dust lives up to its grim name. During the Terran-Vasudan War and the Great War, its isolation and foreboding climate inspired many local rumors of secret GTI bases and mysterious projects."
4742, "(fr)THYATIRA STATION: Thyatira Station is one of the Second Dawn Society's asteroid facilities. In the long term, the SDS intends for Thyatira to become a redundancy for Megiddo Station, giving the organization a fallback should Shivan forces detect and destroy Megiddo. At present, construction on the station has barely begun, although the SDS has indicated a willingness to host civilian refuges in its partially-complete habitation wing."
4743, "(fr)BARNARD'S STAR NODE: Inter-system jump node."
4744, "(fr)Bêta AQUILAE NODE: Inter-system Jump Node."
4745, "(fr)Bêta CYGNI NODE: Inter-system Jump Node."
4746, "(fr)BETELGEUSE NODE: Unstable inter-system Jump Node.\n\nTravel prohibited by GTA Bureau of Inter-System Commerce."
4747, "(fr)LARAMIS NODE: Inter-system jump node. Laramis holds the jump node to Ross 128 and the rest of GTA space."
4748, "(fr)RIBOS NODE: Inter-system Jump Node."
4749, "(fr)VASUDA NODE: Inter-system Jump Node.\n\nGTA fleet units police all traffic through this node, in light of the massive Vasudan refugee influx into Antarès following the Great War. As the only node in Antarès located in a Lagrangian point, this node is an outlier of subspace physics."
4750, "(fr)VEGA NODE: Unstable inter-system Jump Node.\n\nTravel prohibited by GTA Bureau of Inter-System Commerce."
4751, "(fr)WOLF 359 NODE: Inter-system jump node. Sometimes the Wolf 359 node phases inside the Maro Halo, during which time it is unsafe to access."
4752, "(fr)UV CETI: UV Ceti, nicknamed Amatsumikaboshi - literally the 'Dread Star of Heaven' - by early explorers and Boshi by the LNA, is the most violent dwarf star known to Terran civilization. In 1957, UV Ceti's light output increased 75 times in a mere twenty seconds. In ages since, the star has become even more furiously unstable, fluctuating by the hour in diameter and radiance. UV Ceti is prone to apocalyptic coronal mass ejections, perceived by pilots and ship systems alike as a violent EMP felt all the way out to the Oort Cloud. In spite of its danger and inconvenience, the star's extreme energy level has provided the LNA with plenty of scientific data and power for their infrastructure. Some critics still argue that the star is a capricious, lethal time bomb, and that the New Alliance is playing with fire."
4753, "(fr)VIEWING PLATFORM P1-E: This station is positioned to afford an excellent view of Cintilante's spectacular shimmer storms. It is a common vacation destination for middle-class tourists from inside and outside the system, and it has earned a reputation as the system's party central.\n\nIrregular fighter units loyal to the Antarès Federation have been spotted in the vicinity of P1-E."
4754, "(fr)VOSTOK DEEP SPACE RESEARCH LAB: This clandestine facility is built into a cluster of asteroids in the far fringe of the Oort Cloud. Employing a similar philosophy as the SDS asteroid bases, most of the station is tucked away inside the asteroids, with minimal superstructure aside from a network of low-visibility causeways. Vostok was unknown to the GTA until Captain Varner's testimony, after which it was raided by Alliance Marines, revealing it to have been the center of research for INEDAM's controlling AI. It appears that the station was abandoned after infighting regarding the governance of the project."
4755, "(fr)WAYFARER STATION: This Veles-class station was installed in the Luyten system by Galactic Terran Intelligence shortly after the system's discovery. It was intended to serve as a warehouse for classified research and development, but, with the outbreak of the Fourteen Years War, available assets were tasked elsewhere, and the station itself was pressed into a research capacity it was ill-suited for. While the Hades Rebellion was widespread within GTI's Research and Development branch, subsequent investigations have revealed no sign that Wayfarer's crew was involved with or even aware of the insurrection before it began. It appears that the station's remote location and low priority made it a convenient place to relocate those the rebellion saw as threats. With the return of the Galactic Terran Alliance to Luyten, Wayfarer Station has found new life as the hub for GTA forces within the system."
4757, "(fr)WAYSTATION THREE: The LNA's network of Ignis stations serve two important purposes. First, they continually broadcast powerful radio pulses, allowing LNA vessels to calculate more reliable navigational fixes and, in the unlikely event of a misjump, work out their positions upon returning to realspace. Secondly, the stations include life support, hydroponics, and medical equipment rated for ten days' emergency survival for up to 24 Terrans, ensuring a ship in distress always has somewhere to flee to."
4758, "(fr)WAYSTATION TWO: The LNA's network of Ignis stations serve two important purposes. First, they continually broadcast powerful radio pulses, allowing LNA vessels to calculate more reliable navigational fixes and, in the unlikely event of a misjump, work out their positions upon returning to realspace. Secondly, the stations include life support, hydroponics, and medical equipment rated for ten days' emergency survival for up to 24 Terrans, ensuring a ship in distress always has somewhere to flee to."
4759, "(fr)XANTHUS: Though this ball of ice and dust is uninhabitable, its polar ice caps are a prime source of drinking water for the rest of Antarès."
4760, "(fr)RAIDER SCRAPYARD: Located between Luyten's two suns, this massive debris field acts as the source of raw material for new drones. Under the supervision of Ker-Ahes controllers, scrap is broken up, catalogued and sorted, and ultimately made ready for new construction. While there is no obvious fabrication infrastructure at the scrapyard, the sheer scale suggests it must be a critical location. An initial assault against the scrapyard failed with significant casualties, and the hostile environment makes a follow-up strike dicey."
4669, "(fr)ESPERANZA: This gas giant is another gas-mining and gas-refining hub, principally controlled by Exxon-Beckham Orbital Industries."
4727, "(fr)STX EXPLORATION FABRICATION: STX Exploration maintains two Aurora-class fabrication yards, one in Laramis and one in Luyten. These massive stations are the ultimate destination for most of the materials processed by STX. Dozens of internal workshops, from general-purpose manufacturing bays to highly specialized laboratories and cleanrooms, assemble the many finished products in STX's catalog."
4666, "(fr)Antarès STATION: This Arcadia installation will become the center of Antarian government and trade upon its planned completion in 2336. A multi-billion-credit investment, Antarès Station is the capstone of Governor Hirako's campaign to attract legitimate interstellar commerce and reverse Antarès's economic slump. It has come under fire from Antarian particularists, who see it as a waste of taxpayer funds, and as a symbol of unwanted foreign involvement in Antarès's politics and economy.\n\nDue to the recent HoL attacks and disruption of local subspace travel, freighters can only travel to and from Antarès Station in heavily guarded convoys, making part of the journey by sublight."
4665, "(fr)Antarès MINOR: Antarès Major's smaller, younger companion star."
4664, "(fr)Antarès MAJOR AND MINOR: The binary star of the Antarès system. Antarès Major is a supergiant star, and Antarès Minor is its smaller companion. The two stars are bridged by the dangerous Iraklion Corridor."
4663, "(fr)Antarès MAJOR: This supergiant is the brightest star in the Scorpius constellation, once known as 'the heart of the scorpion.'"
4662, "(fr)NEW OCEANIA: This blue gas giant is the center of Terran civilization in Antarès, thanks to its location in Antarès's habitable zone, and its rare gas reserves. The Gulnara moon, the center of trade and government in Antarès, orbits New Oceania."
4661, "(fr)CINTILANTE: This beautiful blue gas giant's sole claim to fame are its frequent 'shimmer storms', meteorological events in the upper atmosphere which produce a singularly beautiful display of color, especially during a full sunset. Local artist Robert Min won the 2311 Aspira Award with a masterwork painting of a large shimmer storm."
4660, "(fr)PORT ZHENG: This rocky, sun-baked world is home to 10.2 million Terran colonists and scattered mining industries. Its largely pro-GTA government welcomes the Intrépide Battlegroup's arrival in-system, hoping that Admiral Po's intervention can restore the safe flow of minerals exports to nearby systems, and salvage its economy. Port Zheng's low population and pro-GTA stance make it an outlier in wider Antarian politics.\n\nContinuing unrest in Antarès has spooked many of the companies which purchase metals from Port Zheng, cutting critically-needed metals exports by 38% in the last week."
4756, "(fr)WAYSTATION ONE: The LNA's network of Ignis stations serve two important purposes. First, they continually broadcast powerful radio pulses, allowing LNA vessels to calculate more reliable navigational fixes and, in the unlikely event of a misjump, work out their positions upon returning to realspace. Secondly, the stations include life support, hydroponics, and medical equipment rated for ten days' emergency survival for up to 24 Terrans, ensuring a ship in distress always has somewhere to flee to."
4658, "(fr)AMANU STATION: The capital of the Luyten New Alliance, Amanu Station is home to both the LNA government and dozens of civilian enterprises that have staked out a claim in the wild Frontière. Built almost organically around the frame of the largest colony vessel in LNA possession, Amanu carefully balances the LNA's utopian ideals with the practical limitations of colonizing a system without habitable planets. The interior of Amanu is a mishmash of shopping concourses and emergency response stations, places of worship and hull breach partitions, nature preserves and evacuation shuttles - although critics are quick to point out that there aren't many places to evacuate to. Tactically, Amanu eschews conventional turrets, favoring a network of Dainsleif-class flak sentries which can, in theory, be repositioned to optimize flak cover. The most important aspect of Amanu's defenses, however, is its oversized air wing, with an estimated two hundred Tyr-class interceptors divided into twelve squadrons. The station integrates with the system's network of communication hubs and science cruisers, allowing very fast fighter response to developments throughout the system."
