1483, "(fr)The EM Pulse missile is conceptually similar to the Stiletto, featuring a warhead tuned for electronics warfare rather than simple hull damage. Unlike the Stiletto, the EMP produced by the weapon is in no way focused, thus creating a shockwave that disrupts the electronic systems of any enemy ships caught within it. EM Pulse missiles are most effective against bombers, as they disrupt the targeting computers for bombs and prevent them from acquiring lock on enemy ships."
1482, "(fr)Electromagnetic Pulse Weapon,
Disorients Targets In Area"
1481, "(fr)GTM-11 EM Pulse"
1480, "(fr)EM Pulse"
1468, "(fr)The Stiletto anti-subsystem bomb features a small electromagnetic pulse-based warhead in its tip, allowing for damage to be caused to enemy subsystems without significantly impacting the hull strength of capital ships. Relying on a tracking system identical to the MX-50 heatseeker, the Stiletto's fire-and-forget nature has made it effective in swarming enemy turrets with large numbers of the missile, often carried on board Zeus or Athena bombers. Attempts are currently being made to cross the subsystem-harming warhead of the Stiletto with the long-range aspect lock of the Ballista to make a more effective anti-turret and anti-subsystem weapon."
1448, "(fr)Anti-Subsystem Bomb,
Fast Reload,
Best Fired In Swarms"
1386, "(fr)GTM-43 Stiletto"
1348, "(fr)Stiletto"
1248, "(fr)The prosaically-named Cluster Bomb is a GTI-designed successor to the Synaptic. Like the Synaptic, the Cluster Bomb splits apart to produce a flurry of explosive $quotebomblets$quote which automatically target nearby fighters and bombers. Unlike the Synaptic, the Cluster Bomb has been well-received by bomber squadrons: it is considerably more effective at destroying fighters outright, and can even inflict meaningful damage to soft targets like transports should the tactical situation require it. However, the Cluster Bomb lacks the Synaptic's ability to disrupt entire fighter wings, and some pilots continue to carry the older weapon as a suppression tool."
1129, "(fr)Synaptic Variant, Wing Attack, Area Effect"
