1126, "(fr)Cluster Bomb"
1125, "(fr)The Synaptic suppression bomb, nicknamed the Earthshaker, is an anti-fighter weapon intended for use by bombers. The Synaptic travels a good distance away from the bomber launching it before detonating, creating a disruptive shockwave that rattles any enemy pilots caught in it. This explosion also helps propel multiple independent $quotebomblets$quote, which automatically target nearby enemy fighters. While classified as a bomb, the Synaptic is only effective in a fighter suppression role, and has very little killing power on its own. Limited numbers of Synaptics remain in production, but it is expected that a next-generation system will replace it."
1124, "(fr)Anti-Fighter Bomb, Wing Attack, Area Effect"
1123, "(fr)GTM-1 Synaptic Bomb"
1122, "(fr)Synaptic"
10661, "(fr)Also known as the STX-3478 Turing, the Locust is a field-expedient refit of the Hornet swarm missile. The original ultraviolet tracking sensor has been wholly replaced with an LNA-designed subspace analytics package. The weapon is a gross violation of GTA guidelines on field modifications, but nevertheless seen as a pragmatic adaption to the developing strategic situation in Luyten.<br/><br/>The Locust operates on the same principle as a 20th-century anti-radiation missile: rather than tracking INEDAM drones directly, it locks onto their subspace communication signatures. INEDAM craft send each other constant updates on their current and planned flight path through continuous, wide-brand subspace broadcasts, both tactically and on a strategic level. A team lead by Dr. Tsega Sarno cross-referenced LNA traffic analysis with data captured from the ICv Gallaecia to come up with a partial $quotephrasebook$quote. By using INEDAM's own navigational data for terminal guidance, the otherwise sluggish GTM-4 has become unerringly accurate in all but the most extreme approach angles. This came at the cost of making the missile useless against other craft$semicolon however, the Locust's multi-aspect capabilities, which allow it to independently track, intercept, and neutralize multiple drones in a single volley is unquestionably worth it.<br/><br/>Simply put, INEDAM itself tells the Locust where to aim."
10660, "(fr)GTiM-4-R Locust"
