1598, "(fr)Anti-Cruiser Bomb,
Long Lock/Reload Time"
1599, "(fr)The Serkr was ostensibly a next-generation anti-cruiser bomb, updating the Tsunami with lessons learned from the Harbinger. The Serkr achieved these objectives, providing a thirty percent increase in killing power as measured by the Ebbesen scale at a somewhat lower price point. However, its real purpose was to provide the GTI insurrection with a heavy torpedo for their Zeus bombers. Thousands of Serkrs were held aboard General Rybak's headquarters, the Jotunheim Installation, and the rebels made tragically effective use of them. While the Serkr plans were destroyed to prevent their capture, operations conducted by the GTD Soyakaze were successful in capturing a handful of Serkrs, which are now being reverse-engineered."
