1034, "(fr)Flail"
1033, "(fr)Based around the GTW-41x Advanced Disruptor, the Disruptor SDG (short for Subsystem Disruption Gun, a new classification for weapons intended to destroy enemy ship systems) improves on its predecessors' success, having the fire rate of the original Disruptor and the shield and subsystem damage of the Advanced Disruptor. While still in the early stages of full-scale adoption, the Disruptor SDG is the current baseline anti-subsystem weapon used by the GTA."
10617, "(fr)GTW-41a Disruptor SDG"
10616, "(fr)Tactical Weapon, Damages Subsystems"
1032, "(fr)GTW-41a Disruptor Cannon SDG"
1031, "(fr)DisruptorSDG"
1030, "(fr)The aging Disruptor is still a baseline weapon in the Terran-Vasudan arsenal. The Disruptor uses a gas-focused krypton laser to excite a bolt of plasma, similar to the old ML-16. Electrical charges within the Disruptor's plasma disrupt targeted subsystems, while the injection of nitrogen dioxide into the emission port minimizes how much effect the Disruptor has against hull plating. This combination of factors together make the Disruptor an ideal weapon for capture operations, where the accidental destruction of a target is an unacceptable outcome. The Disruptor also offers moderate damage to shield systems, and it was employed as a stopgap weapon early in the Shivan Incursion before the Avenger became readily available. The Disruptor has a special ops variant, the GTW-41x Advanced Disruptor, and a successor derived from its successes, the GTW-41a, is being rolled out to all Allied squadrons."
1029, "(fr)Limited Issue
