10614, "(fr)Avenger"
1026, "(fr)The Avenger cannon was introduced near the end of the Fourteen Years War, replacing the aging ML-16. The Avenger utilizes a sheath of ultra-heated unstable plasma wrapped around a core 45mm projectile to deliver a combination of physical and energy-based damage to hostile targets. The unstable nature of the plasma shell grants the Avenger relevatively effective shield penetration, which was an incredible boon during the early Shivan Incursion. While the Avenger is still an effective weapon and extremely energy-efficient, its effectiveness against shields is largely accidental. It has been partially supplanted by newer weapons, including a xaser-excited successor under development by Subach-Innes.<br/><br/>The Avenger was the subject of a minor conspiracy. Lieutenant Alexander McCarthy aboard the GTD Intrépide arranged for the transfer of Avenger prototypes to the Parliamentary Vasudan Navy, ostensibly motivated by the Shivan attack on Ross 128. While the McCarthy defense proved highly controversial, the Alliance did ultimately make the Avenger available to Vasudan forces shortly after the cease-fire.<br/><br/>A variant of the Avenger is typically carried by Medusa and Osiris bombers as a turret weapon."
