10665, "(fr)The GTM MX-64 Rockeye is a faster, more accurate, larger payload version of the MX-60 Roc that was in service during the early Reconstruction period. The missile developed as a result of experimentation by engineers at some of STX Exploration's most isolated mining operations in the systems of Laramis and Luyten 726-BA, followed by incremental upgrades to more effectively shape the missile's blast. The heat-seeking MX-64 Rockeye is now a standard loadout for Terran fighter craft."
