10669, "(fr)Created by the Luyten New Alliance, the DustDevil is a prototype dumbfire missile intended to supplement stockpiles of the GTM Fury. Through advances in chemistry led by Luyten scientist and Nobel Prize winner Thursday Dahlberg, the DustDevil uses a proprietary hydrazine-catalyzed liquid propellant with twice the energy of GTA military-grade propellants used in the Fury. Combining the propellant with a shrunken rocket body and a reconfigured Fury warhead has created an extremely high capacity dumbfire missile that improves on the Fury in every way but cost. The Tyr interceptor used by the LNA as their primary fighter has showcased the effectiveness of first generation DustDevils to great effect, and with improvements in warhead technology, the DustDevil may become a prominent weapon in the Terran-Vasudan arsenal."
