10985, "(fr)Most sorties will end with an order to return to base. Do not leave the field of engagement until you have been authorized to do so."
10937, "(fr)Before we begin, take a look at the left side of the screen. This is the directives list. Directives, controls, and detailed instructions will be shown here."
10938, "(fr)The first function you will learn is targeting. Target my fighter. [Press $T$]

[Look to the right for a summary of the controls you've learned.]"
10939, "(fr)In the lower left hand corner of your HUD is your target view. The top lines display the targeted ship's name and class. It is an Apollo-class fighter much like your own."
10940, "(fr)The next line shows the distance to your target and its speed. Note that my hull integrity is at 100%."
10941, "(fr)Note the brackets around my ship indicating I am your current target. The bracket color indicates my IFF, or Identification, Friend or Foe, status."
10942, "(fr)As I fly out of view, the offscreen indicator will display at the edge of your HUD."
10943, "(fr)The indicator always points at your target. Watch how it moves as I fly around."
10944, "(fr)Notice how the triangles separate as I fly further away. The farther apart they are, the farther you'll have to turn to face your target."
10945, "(fr)Finally, note the number by the indicator. This is the distance to your target."
10946, "(fr)The circular gauge near the bottom of your HUD is the radar. Ships are shown in their IFF color, red for hostile and green for friendly. Ships directly in front of you appear in the radar's center."
10947, "(fr)The circular gauge near the bottom of your HUD is the radar. Ships are shown in their IFF color, yellow for hostile and blue for friendly. Ships directly in front of you appear in the radar's center."
10948, "(fr)Use your main flight controller to turn your ship toward mine. Stop when my ship is in your center reticle."
10949, "(fr)Good. Now stay in that position while I move."
10950, "(fr)Now turn toward my ship again."
10951, "(fr)Next you will learn throttle controls. Follow me this way and match my speed. [Press $M$]"
10952, "(fr)Match my speed now. The next set of controls will only be intuitive if you are moving."
10953, "(fr)Good. Now follow me. Note how your throttle setting automatically changes to match your speed with mine."
10954, "(fr)To the left of the reticle is the speed gauge. The capital M next to the current speed indicates that you are matching speed with your target. The line next to it shows your throttle setting."
10955, "(fr)Use your acceleration key [$A$] to move to within 75 meters of me. Do not collide with my ship."
10956, "(fr)Good. Now decelerate [$Z$] to drop 200 meters behind me."
10957, "(fr)Well done. Now let's practice using the afterburner. [Press $Tab$] Engage your afterburner now, cadet!"
10958, "(fr)The gauge to the left of your speed gauge displays your remaining afterburner reserve. Note that your engines consume it rapidly. Tapping the Afterburner control in quick pulses tends to yield the best results."
10959, "(fr)That extra speed is useful for quick, evasive maneuvers and closing large distances, but is a poor fit for cruising. Maintain your maximum top speed by maxing out your throttle. [Press $\$]"
10960, "(fr)Now come to a complete stop by cutting your throttle. [Press $Backspace$]"
10961, "(fr)Bélier 1 has just warped in. Target it. [Press $T$] You may also try using the 'Nearest Hostile' targeting control. [Press $H$]"
10962, "(fr)Good. Now fly within 100 meters of it, then come to a stop. You can either maximize and then cut the throttle again, or hold down the acceleration key and then come to a stop by releasing it. Either way, your afterburner will help close the distance."
10963, "(fr)Well done. I'm unlocking your weapons now, but hold your fire until I say otherwise."
10964, "(fr)Fire your primary weapon at Bélier 1. Hit it a few times, but do not destroy it. [Press $Left Ctrl$]"
10965, "(fr)You did not have orders to destroy that drone yet, cadet."
10966, "(fr)Now let's learn how to switch and link your primary weapons banks. Your fighter has two sets of Avenger cannons. Currently you are only firing one of them. We'll change that in just a moment."
10967, "(fr)Now destroy Bélier 1 with your linked Avenger cannons! [Press $Left Ctrl$]"
10968, "(fr)Well done. Note that different types of primary cannons can be linked. Now let's take a closer look at some more targeting controls and your secondary weapons."
10969, "(fr)Your weapons loadout is displayed to the right of your reticle. Primary cannons are listed above your secondary missile banks."
10970, "(fr)That control can help you acquire your targets quickly, a vital skill in combat. Note that the Shift key can be used with most targeting controls to cycle targets in reverse order."
10971, "(fr)Good. Furies are dumbfire projectiles. These warheads have no homing system, so they'll fly in the direction in which they are fired. For this reason, they are most effective at close range. Unless your aim is very precise, hitting targets at a distance with the Fury may be difficult$semicolon however, they make up for it in power."
10972, "(fr)Now, destroy Bélier 2 with your Fury Missiles. [Press $Spacebar$] Close your distance if you need to, and make sure to destroy the correct drone."
10973, "(fr)Well done. The Fury may not be as accurate as a heat- or aspect-seeking missile, but a volley of Furies will quickly pulverize an enemy fighter."
10974, "(fr)Now use your secondary weapon selector [$$slash$] to arm your Interceptor missiles. These are aspect-seekers, and require a target lock in order to fire."
10975, "(fr)Now with your Interceptors still selected, target Bélier 3. [Press $H$] Do not fire until told to do so."
10976, "(fr)Notice the red indicator moving towards your target. That's the Aspect Diamond. Once it has moved onto your target, you'll see the lock indicator. This indicates your Interceptors are locked and ready to fire."
10977, "(fr)Now, fire your Interceptors and destroy that drone! Note how fast the Interceptor moves. They deliver quite a payload!"
10978, "(fr)Excellent job. Note the countdown timer in your Weapons Gauge. A missile can only be fired every few seconds. Also note that most aspect-seekers become much slower and won't turn if they fired before lock has been attained. "
10979, "(fr)Now, let's end off by applying what you've learned at the beginning of this session."
10980, "(fr)A waypoint will display on your HUD. Target and fly towards it. Once you are within 25 meters of the waypoint, a new one will appear nearby."
10981, "(fr)This process will repeat several times. Utilize the offscreen indicator, the radar, and your afterburner to fly to each new waypoint as quickly as possible. You will start when the waypoint spawns."
10982, "(fr)Well done. In a combat situation, you may need to rapidly switch targets and respond to new threats. Reaction time and situational awareness are key to your survival."
10983, "(fr)Inability to follow instructions results in immediate failure. Ending simulation..."
10984, "(fr)This concludes module SCS-1-Alpha."
10986, "(fr)Your navigation computer will be programmed with the proper coordinates. All you need to do is engage your subspace drive. Practice with your thruster controls until you feel confident, then jump out to end the simulation. [Press $Alt-J$]"
10987, "(fr)Use your primary weapon selector [Press $.$] to toggle either the other, or both, cannons to fire. Firing both primaries will inflict more damage but will also drain more energy from your fighter's reserves. Select both of your Avengers now."
10988, "(fr)Two more drones have arrived. You have a targeting control which enables you to acquire the nearest hostile target. Using the control repeatedly will cycle through hostile targets in order of their proximity. Try it now. [Press $H$]"
10989, "(fr)Let's make this more interesting. I'm loading an asteroid field into the simulation. You can shoot the asteroids if they get in your way. "
10990, "(fr)Here's some cargo containers for you to avoid. You may destroy them if you like."
10991, "(fr)The finish line is inside the Arcadia installation. Fly through its central hole."
10992, "(fr)Some wings and ships may sometimes have special targeting hotkeys to help you find them more quickly. Use the [F12] control to target the waypoint."
10993, "(fr)We will learn many more targeting controls in future simulations. Use your secondary weapon selector [$$slash$] to arm your bank of Fury missiles. "
