11100, "(fr)Welcome to SCS-1-Gamma, Escort Training. In this simulation, you will practice interacting with warships in both an escort and surgical strike capacity."
11101, "(fr)You may notice some new weapons in your loadout. The Banshee is an electromagnetic weapon offering excellent shield damage. With high power draw and only moderate effectiveness against hull armor, the Banshee is best coupled with a generalist weapon like the Avenger."
11102, "(fr)Many bombers rely on heavy shields, making the Banshee a natural choice for interceptor pilots. Use it to punch a hole through enemy shields before switching to another weapon."
11103, "(fr)The Phoenix V is a long-ranged aspect seeking missile. With high marks for range and damage and an advanced tracking system, the Phoenix V excels at destroying enemy strikecraft before they come close enough to return fire."
11104, "(fr)While typically employed against bombers, the Phoenix is also effective against fighters and subsystems. It suffers from a relatively long lock time and a brief delay while its guidance computer initializes, making it ineffective in a dogfight."
11105, "(fr)I've added an Amazon drone to the simulation. Destroy it with a Phoenix missile."
11106, "(fr)Good. I'm adding a larger drone now. Acquire aspect lock on its engine subsystem. [Press $S$]"
11107, "(fr)Disable Poissons 2. A single Phoenix V should do the trick."
11108, "(fr)Good. Notice how Poissons 2 is marked as disabled on your target view. Now destroy Poissons 2. Try using both your Banshee and Avenger and compare how they perform."
11109, "(fr)Now that you're familiar with your weapons, I'm adding the GTC Heroic to the simulation. I've also restored your missiles."
11110, "(fr)Important ships are tracked on your escort list. Target the Heroic with your escort targeting control. [Press $E$]"
11111, "(fr)The Heroic is a Fenris-class strike cruiser. Unlike the defensively-oriented Leviathan, the Fenris is fast, but relatively fragile. Allied pilots are often called on to protect them. Form up on the Heroic now."
11112, "(fr)I suggest matching speeds with the Heroic. [Press $M$] The first enemies will arrive momentarily."
11113, "(fr)A special targeting control is available to find ships attacking your target. With the Heroic targeted, try it now. [Press $G$]"
11114, "(fr)Good. Now destroy Gémeaux wing."
11115, "(fr)The next wave will contain Falcon fighters. The Falcon is one of the heaviest fighters allowed to civilian operators. The Alliance would like to outlaw them to keep them out of pirate hands$semicolon for the time being, they still fulfill an important role holding back Hammer of Light raiders."
11116, "(fr)Four Falcons, designated Buri, have arrived. Set your Phoenix Vs to double-fire mode and snipe them at range. Make sure you have auto-targeting [$Alt-H$] enabled, and use your Banshee to destroy their shields."
11117, "(fr)Well done. Before we proceed to the next phase, let's resupply your fighter with missiles. This time, I won't do an simulator magic. Instead, you're going to call in a support ship. Open your comms board and call for rearm. [Press $C$, 5]"
11118, "(fr)Come to a complete stop and wait for the support ship to dock. If you want to monitor its progress, a special control is available. [Press $Alt-R$]"
11119, "(fr)Since the cease-fire with the Parliamentary Vasudan Empire, our Centaur-class support ship and their Scarab have been made mutually compatible. During joint operations, you may be rearmed by a Scarab."
11120, "(fr)Your missile supply has been restored to full. Support ships can also repair your subsystems, but cannot repair your hull."
11121, "(fr)Once called in, support ships will generally wait nearby until they're needed again. To be polite, let's tell this one to depart. [Press $C$, 1, 1, 3]"
11122, "(fr)Return to escort position alongside the Heroic. Use the escort targeting control [$E$] if you need help finding it."
11124, "(fr)Well done. You may have noticed the Heroic's plasma turrets helping you shoot down bombs. Knowing how to effectively attack turrets is a hallmark of a skilled bomber pilot, and a task which fighters are often called upon to help with. We'll go over this momentarily."
11125, "(fr)I've reset the Heroic's hull integrity to full, along with yours."
11126, "(fr)We're about to be attacked by a wing of Zeus bombers. They'll launch Tsunami bombs, just like before. The Heroic can intercept their bombs, but will need your help against the bombers."
11127, "(fr)Tyr wing is arriving. Set your Phoenix missiles to dual-fire and try to snipe one of them, then use your afterburners to close the distance. Remember to use your Banshees against their shields."
11128, "(fr)All Zeus bombers destroyed. Well done. Again, I've reset your hull integrity."
11129, "(fr)You seem to have taken some damage in that fight. Bombs are usually ineffective against shields, but they can be deadly if your shields are breached. We'll go over shield management in a later tutorial. For now, I've reset your hull integrity."
11130, "(fr)There are a few more targeting controls to go over. You've already seen the subsystem targeting control [$S$] and turret targeting control [$K$]. Target the Heroic, then its mortar turret."
11131, "(fr)Well done. You'll typically use this control to target turrets you plan on attacking. There's another control to target the subsystem or turret under your center reticle. Use it to target the Heroic's radar dish. [Press $V$]"
11132, "(fr)Now use the same control to target the Heroic's mortar turret again."
11133, "(fr)Well done. You're about to put these controls to good use."
11134, "(fr)A hostile Leviathan cruiser, the Villainous, has come on sensors. A Leviathan is tougher than a Fenris, so we'll need to even the odds. Use your Phoenix missiles to destroy the Villainous' weapon subsystem."
11135, "(fr)Remember that destroying a warship's weapon system will degrade its turrets' accuracy, but not stop them altogether. Destroy the Villainous' mortar turret."
11136, "(fr)The Villainous is retreating into subspace, and this sector of space is secure for now. Well done. Enter subspace to end this simulator session when ready."
11155, "(fr)Route all energy from shields"
